%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eturn%20off%20a%20plane's%20engines%20mid-flight%3C%2Fa%3E%20despite%20conforming%20to%20the%20aviation%20industry's%20strict%20safety%20regulations%20%E2%80%94%20highlighting%20the%20potential%20havoc%20airline%20personnel%20can%20wreak%20even%20while%20operating%20within%20the%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Alaska%20Airlines%20pilot%20was%20accused%20of%20trying%20to%20shut%20off%20the%20plane%20engines%20and%20later%20attempting%20to%20grab%20the%20handle%20of%20an%20emergency%20door%20during%20Alaska%20Airlines%20Flight%202059%20operated%20by%20Horizon%20Air%20from%20Everett%2C%20Washington%2C%20to%20San%20Francisco%2C%20California%20on%20Sunday%2C%20according%20to%20federal%20and%20state%20court%20documents%20reviewed%20by%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20off-duty%20pilot%2C%20Joseph%20Emerson%2C%20who%20told%20authorities%20he%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foff-duty-pilot-charged-alaska-airlines-court-documents-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etaken%20psychedelic%20mushrooms%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20first%20time%20about%2048%20hours%20prior%20to%20the%20flight%2C%20was%20charged%20Tuesday%20with%20one%20federal%20count%20of%20interfering%20with%20flight%20crew%20members%20and%20attendants%2C%20as%20well%20as%20dozens%20of%20state%20charges%20of%20attempted%20murder%20and%20reckless%20endangerment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmerson%2C%2044%2C%20pleaded%20not%20guilty%20in%20court%20on%20Tuesday.%20His%20attorney%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20on-duty%20pilots%20who%20were%20operating%20the%20plane%20carrying%2080%20passengers%20and%20four%20crew%20members%20were%20able%20to%20subdue%20Emerson%20in%20the%20cockpit%20before%20he%20was%20able%20to%20send%20the%20plane%20into%20free%20fall%2C%20but%20the%20bizarre%20incident%20lays%20bare%20the%20ways%20in%20which%20aviation%20insiders%20are%20able%20to%20skirt%20the%20industry's%20stringent%20safety%20procedures%2C%20experts%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPost-9%2F11%20protections%20have%20made%20our%20cockpits%20very%20secure%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Anthony%20Brickhouse%2C%20an%20air%20safety%20investigator%20and%20associate%20professor%20at%20Embry%20Riddle%20Aeronautical%20University.%20%26quot%3BBut%20those%20procedures%20were%20to%20protect%20flight%20crew%20from%20passengers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20'jump%20seat'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEmerson%20was%20riding%20in%20the%20plane's%20cockpit%20%26quot%3Bjump%20seat%26quot%3B%20when%20he%20began%20acting%20strangely%2C%20according%20to%20federal%20court%20documents.%20The%20jump%20seat%20%E2%80%94%20or%20sometimes%20seats%20depending%20on%20the%20size%20of%20the%20aircraft%20%E2%80%94%20is%20located%20behind%20the%20pilots'%20seats%2C%20giving%20Emerson%20easy%20access%20to%20the%20fire%20handles%20located%20inside%20the%20cockpit%20which%20activate%20the%20plane's%20emergency%20fire%20suppression%20system%20and%20cut%20off%20fuel%20from%20the%20engines%2C%20according%20to%20federal%20court%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20jump%20seat%20is%20often%20used%20by%20off-duty%20pilots%20to%20travel%20to%20and%20from%20work%2C%20as%20well%20as%20industry%20inspectors%20and%20professionals%2C%20Brickhouse%20said.%20The%20extra%20seat%20allows%20pilots%20to%20easily%20move%20between%20destinations%20without%20the%20airline%20having%20to%20bump%20a%20paying%20passenger%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fairline-security-safety-insider-threat-emerson-90d1285c4df305e59add39e3d5a93424%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Associated%20Press%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225813%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Pilots%20conduct%20a%20pre-flight%20check%20in%20the%20cockpit%20of%20a%20jet%20before%20taking%20off%20from%20Dallas%20Fort%20Worth%20airport%20in%20Grapevine%2C%20Texas%2C%20on%20Dec.%202%2C%202020.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653860350487ff031cad7402%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223669%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPilots%20conduct%20a%20pre-flight%20check%20in%20the%20cockpit%20of%20a%20jet%20before%20taking%20off%20from%20Dallas%20Fort%20Worth%20airport%20in%20Grapevine%2C%20Texas%2C%20on%20Dec.%202%2C%202020.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FLM%20Otero%2C%20File%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGaining%20access%20to%20the%20jump%20seat%2C%20however%2C%20requires%20vetting%2C%20Brickhouse%20said.%20Airlines%20have%20to%20approve%20any%20person%20who%20sits%20in%20the%20jump%20seat%20and%20off-duty%20pilots%20must%20present%20their%20credentials%20to%20the%20crew%2C%20according%20to%20The%20AP%3B%20a%20flight's%20captain%20also%20has%20final%20say%20over%20any%20additional%20people%20riding%20in%20the%20cockpit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20far%20as%20we%20know%2C%20this%20pilot%20was%20perfectly%20legal%20and%20perfectly%20certified%20to%20be%20riding%20in%20the%20jump%20seat%2C%26quot%3B%20Brickhouse%20said%20of%20Emerson.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20on-duty%20pilots%20later%20told%20police%20they%20didn't%20notice%20anything%20strange%20about%20Emerson's%20behavior%20prior%20to%20takeoff.%20The%20pilots%20said%20they%20talked%20casually%20with%20him%20about%20different%20types%20of%20aircraft%20and%20the%20weather%2C%20according%20to%20a%20criminal%20complaint.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOnce%20you're%20in%20that%20cockpit%2C%20you're%20someone%20who%20is%20supposed%20to%20be%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20Brickhouse%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPilot%20psychology%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20on-duty%20pilots%20later%20told%20authorities%20that%20Emerson%20was%20behaving%20normally%20for%20the%20first%20half%20of%20the%20flight%20until%20he%20tossed%20his%20headset%20across%20the%20cockpit%20and%20said%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falaska-airlines-off-duty-pilot-accused-shut-plane-engines-details-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EI'm%20not%20okay.%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20He%20then%20reached%20up%20and%20grabbed%20the%20red%20fire%20handles%20and%20pulled%20them%20down%2C%20the%20criminal%20complaint%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20on-duty%20pilots%20grabbed%20Emerson's%20wrist%20while%20the%20other%20declared%20an%20in-flight%20emergency%2C%20according%20to%20court%20documents.%20They%20briefly%20wrestled%20with%20Emerson%20before%20he%20settled%20down.%20He%20then%20left%20the%20cockpit%20and%20was%20restrained%20by%20the%20flight%20crew%2C%20according%20to%20court%20records.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20of%20the%20nature%20of%20their%20profession%2C%20pilots%20have%20to%20undergo%20a%20psychological%20screening%20during%20their%20regular%20medical%20exams%2C%20the%20AP%20reported.%20Emerson%20had%20his%20most%20recent%20exam%20in%20September%2C%20according%20to%20the%20outlet%2C%20which%20cited%20Federal%20Aviation%20Administration%20records.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20these%20required%20exams%2C%20FAA-approved%20medical%20examiners%20interview%20the%20pilot%20and%20note%20whether%20they%20have%20received%20any%20psychiatric%20treatment%20and%20any%20medications%20they're%20taking%2C%20The%20AP%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20seemingly%20little%20in%20Emerson's%20immediately%20accessible%20public%20record%20or%20history%20to%20indicate%20he%20would%20be%20involved%20in%20Sunday's%20incident%2C%20according%20to%20media%20reports.%20He%20had%20completed%20all%20of%20his%20required%20professional%20certifications%20and%20had%20no%20criminal%20record%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F10%2F24%2Fus%2Falaska-airlines-off-duty-pilot-arraignment.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFriends%20and%20former%20flying%20colleagues%20of%20Emerson's%20told%20The%20AP%20he%20was%20a%20nice%2C%20normal-seeming%20gu