n%20high%20above%20the%20MS%20Voyager%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652b4e3f6561dd877e7add7e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222160%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20illustration%20of%20the%20Spaceship%20Neptune%20launching%20off%20the%20MS%20Voyager%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Space%20Perspectives%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPer%20Space%20Perspective%2C%20the%20mobile%20launch%20site%20is%20ideal%20because%20it%20allows%20crews%20to%20move%20and%20avoid%20inclement%20weather%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Spaceship%20Neptune%20will%20also%20return%20to%20the%20ship%20after%20landing%20in%20the%20Atlantic%20Ocean%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20Florida%2C%20where%20crews%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-commando-who-fell-from-speedboat-under-fire-describes-survival-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espeedboats%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20rush%20to%20collect%20the%20ship%20and%20its%20passengers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPoynter%20told%20Insider%20that%20previous%20tests%20of%20the%20prototype%20vessel%20have%20resulted%20in%20a%20reasonably%20accurate%20flight%20path%2C%20meaning%20that%20the%20capsule%20lands%20near%20the%20MS%20Voyager.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20six-hour%20adventure%20will%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnet-zero-carbon-neutral-negative-climate-company-goals-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecarbon%20neutral%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20from%20the%20vehicle%20that%20transports%20guests%20to%20the%20ship%20to%20the%20flight%20itself%2C%20the%20company%20said%20in%20a%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ETons%20of%20industries%20have%20their%20eyes%20on%20the%20potential%20of%20high-altitude%20balloons.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225544%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22CHARLOTTE%2C%20USA%20-%20FEBRUARY%204%3A%20Chinese%20spy%20balloon%20flies%20above%20in%20Charlotte%20NC%2C%20United%20States%20on%20February%2004%2C%20202