iled%20Treasury%20auction%20soon%2C%20a%20Columbia%20Business%20School%20professor%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EFears%20about%20mounting%20US%20debt%20have%20already%20worried%20investors%2C%20contributing%20to%20a%20sell-off%20in%20bonds.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EIn%20a%20failed%20auction%2C%20the%20Fed%20would%20have%20to%20step%20in%20and%20buy%20US%20bonds%2C%20fanning%20inflation.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20two%20levers%20that%20policymakers%20use%20to%20toggle%20the%20amount%20of%20money%20in%20the%20markets%3A%20monetary%20policy%20and%20fiscal%20policy.%20But%20what%20happens%20when%20one%20creates%20a%20problem%20for%20the%20other%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Columbia%20Business%20School%20professor%20Charles%20Calomiris%2C%20it's%20a%20dilemma%20the%20US%20is%20facing%20right%20now.%20Soon%20enough%2C%20the%20federal%20deficit%20is%20going%20to%20swell%20to%20the%20point%20where%20no%20one%20will%20want%20to%20take%20on%20government-issued%20debt%2C%20and%20the%20only%20people%20who%20will%20save%20a%20failed%20Treasury%20auction%20will%20be%20the%20central%20bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20possibilities%20that's%20driving%20bond%20yields%20higher%20is%20the%20concerns%20about%20inflation%20risk%20related%20to%20the%20cumulative%20effect%20of%20debt%2C%26quot%3B%20Calomiris%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2Fvideo%2F2023%2F10%2F23%2Fcumulative-effect-of-the-deficit-could-force-the-fed-to-buy-debt-says-columbias-charles-calomiris.html%5C%22%3ECNBC%20interview%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Monday.%20%26quot%3BThe%20possibility%20that%20the%20cumulative%20effect%20of%20deficits%20will%20cause%20money%20printing%20to%20result%20from%20the%20unwillingness%20of%20people%20to%20bear%20increasing%20amounts%20of%20government%20debt%2C%20which%20forces%20the%20Fed%20to%20step%20in%20and%20purchase%20the%20debt%2C%20that%20is%2C%20effectively%2C%20printing%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20how%20it