ly%20key%20American%20bases%20and%20operations%20centers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22649%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20map%20of%20China's%20fielded%20conventional%20strike%20capabilities%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653827da0487ff031cad3a22%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22612%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20map%20of%20China's%20fielded%20conventional%20strike%20capabilities%3Cp%3EDepartment%20of%20Defense%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that's%20been%20a%20priority%20for%20China%20for%20years%20now.%20In%202017%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rand.org%2Fcontent%2Fdam%2Frand%2Fpubs%2Fresearch_reports%2FRR300%2FRR392%2FRAND_RR392.pdf%5C%22%3ERAND%20assessed%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20key%20US%20facilities%20specifically%20in%20Japan%20could%20already%20be%20within%20range%20of%20thousands%20of%20accurate%20Chinese%20ballistic%20and%20cruise%20missiles%20that%20could%20be%20hard%20to%20counter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%201996%2C%20the%20PLA%20was%20just%20beginning%20to%20develop%20conventionally%20armed%20ballistic%20missiles%20and%20had%20only%20a%20few%20dozen%20relatively%20inaccurate%20conventionally%20armed%20short-range%20missiles%20that%20could%20reach%20targets%20in%20Taiwan%20or%20Korea%2C%20but%20not%20US%20bases%20in%20Japan%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20RAND%20report%20said.%20%26quot%3BBy%202015%2C%20however%2C%20the%20PLA's%20Second%20Artillery%20had%20deployed%20more%20than%201%2C200%20conventionally%20armed%20ballistic%20missiles%2C%20including%20the%20DF-21C%20with%20the%20range%20to%20attack%20targets%20throughout%20Japan.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20China%20has%20also%20prioritized%20accuracy%20in%20addition%20to%20numbers.%20As%20Shugart%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnas.org%2Fpublications%2Freports%2Ffirst-strike-chinas-missile-threat-to-u-s-bases-to-asia%5C%22%3Ewrote%20in%202017%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3Bby%20marrying%20great%20accuracy%20with%20numerous%20ballistic%20missiles%2C%20China%20may%20have%20developed%20a%20capability%20that%20the%20Soviet%20armed%20forces%20never%20had%3A%20the%20ability%20to%20strike%20effectively%2C%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20minutes%2C%20US%20and%20allied%20bases%2C%20logistical%20facilities%2C%20and%20command%20centers%20without%20resorting%20to%20the%20use%20of%20nuclear%20weapons%2C%20and%20without%20having%20established%20air%20superiority.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225244%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22US%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20meets%20with%20China's%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20during%20a%20virtual%20summit%20from%20the%20Roosevelt%20Room%20of%20the%20White%20House%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20November%2015%2C%202021.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64fe9fda3d3923001977ddb2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223496%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20meets%20with%20China's%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20during%20a%20virtual%20summit%20from%20the%20Roosevelt%20Room%20of%20the%20White%20House%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20November%2015%2C%202021.%3Cp%3EMandel%20Ngan%2FAFP%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bolstering%20of%20China's%20stockpile%20of%20missiles%20capable%20of%20hitting%20US%20targets%20across%20Japan%20is%20likely%20both%20a%20flex%20of%20military%20might%20and%20a%20deterrent%20against%20American%20forces%20in%20the%20region%2C%20and%20it%20also%20comes%20at%20a%20near-frigid%20point%20in%20PRC%20and%20US%20relations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%202022%2C%20the%20PLA%20largely%20denied%2C%20cancelled%2C%20and%20ignored%20recurring%20bilateral%20engagements%20and%20DoD%20requests%20for%20communication%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Pentagon%20included%20in%20their%20report.%20%26quot%3BThe%20PLA's%20refusal%20to%20engage%20with%20DoD%20has%20largely%20continued%20in%202023%26quot%3B%20and%2C%20along%20with%20its%20%26quot%3Bincreasing