e%20even%20claimed%20that%20Amazon's%20algorithm%20moved%20the%20bizarre%20product%20into%20its%20drinks%20category%20on%20the%20site%20after%20he%20had%20put%20it%20in%20the%20%26quot%3BRefillable%20Pump%20Dispense%26quot%3B%20category.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMr%20Butler%20got%20some%20of%20his%20friends%20to%20purchase%20the%20product%20and%20felt%20%26quot%3Binitially%20really%20excited%20and%20found%20it%20very%20funny%26quot%3B.%20However%2C%20he%20added%20that%20when%20real%20people%20started%20trying%20to%20buy%20the%20product%2C%20he%20felt%20a%20bit%20%26quot%3Bscared%26quot%3B.%20Mr%20Butler%20reportedly%20claimed%20that%20he%20never%20sold%20the%20item%20to%20any%20real%20customers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlso%20read%20%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fnasa-unable-to-remove-remaining-asteroid-sample-from-container-working-on-new-ways-4508991%5C%22%3ENASA%20Unable%20To%20Remove%20Remaining%20Asteroid%20Sample%20From%20Container%2C%20Working%20On%20New%20Ways%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMr%20Butler%20said%20that%20he%20decided%20to%20make%20the%20documentary%20and%20list%20the%20bottles%20on%20Amazon%20to%20help%20shed%20some%20light%20on%20the%20company's%20impact%20on%20society%2C%20which%20includes%20its%20workers%20who%20stated%20that%20they%20were%20forced%20to%20urinate%20in%20bottles%20so%20that%20they%20could%20meet%20strict%20deadlines.%20He%20even%20spoke%20to%20some%20workers%20who%20said%20that%20they%20would%20be%20urinating%20in%20bottles%20to%20meet%20delivery%20deadlines%20on%20the%20e-commerce%20site.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20reacting%20to%20the%20story%20of%20%26quot%3BRelease%26quot%3B%20being%20sold%20on%20the%20e-commerce%20site%2C%20Amazon%20said%20that%20a%20distorted%20picture%20of%20their%20process%20has%20been%20shown%20to%20the%20world.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vice.com%2Fen%2Farticle%2Fz3mge3%2Fselling-bottles-of-amazon-