ion%20for%20the%20marginalised%20social%20groups.%20This%20is%20a%20petty%20and%20cursory%20remark%20as%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20act%20for%20religious%20conversion%20created%20a%20bridging%20dialogue%20between%20modernity%20and%20tradition%20and%20suggested%20why%20substantive%20ethical%20foundations%20are%20a%20prerequisite%20to%20building%20a%20new%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20popular%20to%20characterise%20Ambedkar%20as%20a%20modern%20liberal%20thinker%20as%20he%20has%20often%20endorsed%20the%20western%20ideals%20to%20visualise%20India%E2%80%99s%20future.%20His%20drafting%20of%20the%20newly%20independent%20nation%E2%80%99s%20constitution%20is%20often%20understood%20as%20his%20validation%20to%20modern%20progressive%20values%20and%20its%20normative%20goals.%20India%E2%80%99s%20federal%20structure%2C%20parliamentary%20democracy%2C%20the%20infallible%20powers%20of%20the%20judiciary%2C%20university%20education%2C%20etc.%2C%20supplement%20the%20idea%20that%20India%20is%20an%20integral%20part%20of%20the%20western%20model%20of%20development%20and%20may%20progress%20similar%20to%20the%20advances%20made%20by%20the%20European%20nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThough%20Ambedkar%20admired%20the%20emancipatory%20values%20of%20the%20modern%20liberal%20project%2C%20he%20was%20not%20convinced%20that%20it%20has%20ample%20capacity%20to%20transform%20the%20Indian%20social%20order%20radically.%20Interestingly%2C%20such%20critical%20realisation%20did%20not%20influence%20Ambedkar%20to%20adopt%20the%20Marxist%20militant%20alternative%20to%20bring%20social%20and%20political%20change.%20Instead%2C%20he%20looked%20into%20India%E2%80%99s%20ancient%20philosophical%20traditions%20and%20suggested%20that%20the%20revival%20of%20Buddhism%20would%20humanise%20the%20current%20social%20order%20better%20and%20make%20it%20compatible%20to%20modernist%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F24144549%2FDr._Ambedkar_delivering_speech_during_conversion.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22925%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F24144549%2FDr._Ambedkar_delivering_speech_during_conversion.jpg%20456w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F24144549%2FDr._Ambedkar_delivering_speech_during_conversion-300x214.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-681534%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22659%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAmbedkar%20delivering%20speech%20during%20conversion%2C%20Nagpur%2C%20October%2014%2C%201956.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWestern%20modernity%20and%20the%20ideals%20of%20Indian%20nationalism%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmbedkar%20equally%20understood%20that%20the%20ideals%20of%20nationalism%20in%20India%20are%20not%20based%20on%20secular%20values%20but%20are%20constructed%20around%20ancient%20Hindu%20civilisational%20ethos.%20The%20arrival%20of%20Gandhi%20in%20the%20national%20independence%20movement%20as%20a%20maverick%20leader%20also%20paved%20the%20crucial%20entry%20to%20the%20Hindu%20religious%20ideas%2C%20rituals%2C%20and%20symbols%20to%20mobilise%20the%20common%20masses.%20Under%20his%20leadership%2C%20it%20was%20questioned%20how%20western%20modernity%20could%20build%20an%20indigenous%20resistance%20based%20on%20the%20values%20that%20are%20integral%20to%20Hindu%20traditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20right-wing%20cultural%20nationalism%20is%20also%20cultivated%20on%20a%20similar%20premise%2C%20with%20an%20extra%20layer%20of%20patriarchal%20force%20and%20xenophobic%20tendencies.%20Between%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20nationalism%20based%20on%20communal%20harmony%20and%20Savarkar%E2%80%99s%20majoritarian%20Hindutva%20nationalism%2C%20there%20is%20a%20visible%20difference.%20However%2C%20both%20were%20convinced%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20national%20identity%20must%20be%20based%20upon%20certain%20Hindu%20cultural%20idioms.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmbedkar%20noticed%20that%20the%20Hindu%20identity%2C%20its%20political%20ideology%2C%20and%20the%20ancient%20cultural%20motifs%20are%20integral%20characteristics%20of%20Indian%20nationalism.%20Though%20this%20is%20a%20powerful%20imagination%2C%20Ambedkar%20experienced%20that%20the%20socially%20marginalised%20communities%2C%20especially%20the%20Dalits%2C%20feel%20alienated%20and%20depressed%20in%20such%20%E2%80%98Brahmanical%E2%80%99%20cultural%20milieu.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWithin%20the%20Hindu%20caste%20matrix%2C%20the%20people%20belonging%20to%20the%20Dalit%20community%20are%20not%20seen%20as%20equal%20beings%20but%20are%20condemned%20as%20%E2%80%9Cimpure%20bodies%E2%80%9D%2C%20forced%20to%20suffer%20a%20precarious%20life%20cycle%20of%20poverty%2C%20exclusion%2C%20and%20violence.%20He%20explained%20that%20the%20Hindus%20are%20afflicted%20by%20the%20caste%20system%20that%20often%20prevents%20them%20from%20organising%20based%20on%20the%20values%20of%20fraternity%20and%20equality.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENationalism%20based%20on%20Hindu%20religious%20symbols%20creates%20a%20powerful%20political%20rhetoric%20of%20unity.%20Nevertheless%2C%20Ambedkar%20often%20questioned%20its%20capacity%20to%20challenge%20the%20Brahmanical%20hegemony%20and%20transform%20the%20oppressive%20social%20relationships.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDistinct%20from%20the%20cultural%20nationalism%20project%20that%20forcefully%20includes%20the%20Dalits%20as%20integral%20to%20Hindu%20unity%2C%20without%20altering%20the%20social%20hierarchies%2C%20the%20modern%20state%20promises%20equal%20treatment%20to%20its%20citizens%20and%20exclusive%20opportunities%20and%20protections%20to%20emancipate%20the%20worst-off%20social%20groups.%20Ambedkar%20diagnosed%20that%20the%20Hindu%20%E2%80%9Cuntouchable%E2%80%9D%20identity%20is%20depressing%20and%20hardly%20incites%20confidence%3B%20instead%2C%20it%20discourages%20the%20Dalit%20community%20to%20participate%20in%20modern%20secular%20spaces%20with%20a%20robust%20feeling%20of%20individuality.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20state%20promises%20them%20protections%20and%20safeguards%2C%20in%20the%20general%20public%20life%2C%20the%20Dalit%20community%20has%20to%20face%20brutal%20Brahmanical%20gaze%20that%20disallows%20a%20person%20to%20perform%20as%20a%20right-bearing%20equal%20citizen.%20Ambedkar%20pondered%20for%20decades%20to%20find%20a%20solution%20to%20this%20perpetual%20embargo.%20Mass%20conversion%20to%20Buddhism%20emerged%20as%20a%20revolutionary%20solution%20to%20such%20a%20puzzle.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20revolutionary%20solution%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmbedkar%20embraced%20Buddhism%20so%20that%20the%20Dalits%20can%20enjoy%20the%20profits%20of%20modern%20development%20with%20confidence%20and%20a%20heightened%20sense%20of%20equality.%20Rejection%20of%20Hinduism%20also%20means%20rejection%20of%20the%20depressing%20social%20psychology%20that%20was%20forced%20upon%20the%20Dalits.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20Ambedkar%20offered%20them%20a%20convincing%20historic%20legend%20that%20the%20Dalits%20were%20the%20ruling%20elites%20in%20the%20ancient%20past%20and%20only%20after%20getting%20defeated%20by%20the%20cunning%20and%20treacherous%20Brahmanical%20conspiracy%2C%20they%20were%20forced%20into%20servility%20and%20later%20marked%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9Cuntouchables%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20adopting%20the%20neo-Buddhist%20identity%20is%20not%20just%20a%20conversion%20ploy%20to%20create%20a%20minority%20religion%20but%20it%20is%20the%20reclamation%20of%20the%20Dalit%20community%E2%80%99s%20glorious%20past%2C%20its%20intellectual%20legacies%2C%20and%20the%20lost%20ethical%20vision.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20distinct%20from%20the%20Brahmanical%20social%20ideology%2C%20which%20is%20antithetical%20to%20the%20modern%20egalitarian%20virtues%2C%20Ambedkar%20thought%20that%20the%20teachings%20of%20Buddha%20would%20supplement%20the%20liberal%20democratic%20ideals.%20He%20believed%20that%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20better%20future%2C%20a%20rapid%20modernisation%20of%20the%20social%20and%20economic%20spheres%20is%20a%20must.%20In%20order%20to%20enjoy%20the%20benefits%20of%20capitalist%20development%20and%20democracy%2C%20an%20individual%20shall%20be%20free%20from%20the%20social%20compartments%20and%20have%20the%20ability%20to%20enter%20into%20the%20modern%20realm%20as%20a%20thinking%20and%20rational%20being.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20observed%20that%20the%20belief%20in%20caste%20identity%20hampers%20such%20individuality%20and%20disturbs%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20fraternal%20milieu.%20He%20hoped%20that%20Buddhism%20will%20help%20an%20individual%20to%20escape%20the%20caste%20fixity%20and%20motivate%20them%20to%20enjoy%20the%20benefits%20of%20modernity%20as%20a%20free%20intellectual%20being.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThird%2C%20with%20Buddhism%2C%20Ambedkar%20also%20revitalised%20India%E2%80%99s%20cultural%20past%20and%20made%20it%20relevant%20in%20the%20modern%20times.%20Contrary%20to%20the%20Left-Marxist%E2%80%99s%20anathema%20towards%20the%20application%20of%20religion%20in%20modern%20times%2C%20Ambedkar%20looked%20at%20religion%20as%20a%20necessary%20moral%20component%20that%20provides%20meaning%20to%20human%20existence.%20However%2C%20he%20also%20remained%20critical%20towards%20the%20right-wing%E2%80%99s%20usage%20of%20religion%20in%20the%20political%20processes.%20He%20suggested%20that%20the%20religious%20teachings%20shall%20compliment%20the%20modern%20ethics%20of%20liberty%2C%20equality%2C%20and%20fraternity%20and%20found%20that%20the%20Hindu%20political%20ideology%20is%20hate-based%2C%20cherishes%20the%20Brahmanical%20cultural%20values%2C%20and%20is%20non-committal%20towards%20the%20annihilation%20of%20the%20oppressive%20caste%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Ambedkar%2C%20Buddhism%2C%20in%20contrast%2C%20upholds%20humanism%2C%20individual%20freedom%2C%20and%20a%20peaceful%20coexistence%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20is%20suitable%20for%20the%20modern%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmbedkar%20recognised%20that%20religious%20identity%20is%20crucial%20for%20creating%20ethical%20social%20and%20political%20affairs%20as%20humans%20are%20historically%20embedded%20into%20such%20phenomena.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20western%20modernity%20belittles%20human%20association%20with%20religious%20rituals%20or%20their%20spiritual%20quests.%20It%20seeks%20to%20establish%20an%20individual-centric%20secular%20polity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmbedkar%20bridged%20this%20gap%20between%20the%20two%20worlds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWith%20his%20historic%20conversion%20to%20Buddhism%2C%20Ambedkar%20offered%20that%20religious%20teachings%20can%20help%20the%20individual%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20modern%20realm%20as%20a%20competent%20moral%20individual%2C%20motivated%20to%20build%20a%20social%20order%20sans%20discrimination%20and%20prejudices.%20The%20Buddhist%20history%20and%20thoughts%20are%20equally%20suited%20for%20the%20modern%20times%20and%20would%20help%20the%20new%20nation%20to%20build%20its%20citadel%20on%20the%20ancient%20ethical%20foundation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20maverick%20arrival%20of%20the%20neo-Buddhist%20community%20in%20Maharashtra%20as%20a%20powerful%20political%20and%20intellectual%20group%20and%20its%20robust%20presence%20in%20the%20middle-class%20domain%20today%20offers%20a%20glimpse%20that%20Ambedkar%20was%20accurate%20about%20his%20prediction.%20However%2C%20on%20the%20flip%20side%2C%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20Buddhist%20mission%20was%20restricted%20to%20particular%20regions%20and%20did%20not%20emerge%20as%20a%20capable%20force%20to%20challenge%20the%20Hindutva%20hegemony.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20the%20right-wing%20ideological%20assertions%20and%20cultural%20strategies%20influenced%20the%20socially%20deprived%20masses%20and%20integrated%20them%20into%20its%20communal%20rhetoric.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EImportantly%2C%20with%20the%20rise%20of%20Hindutva-based%20communal%20identity%2C%20the%20caste-based%20deprived%20social%20identities%20have%20not%20dried%20away%2C%20instead%20they%20have%20gained%20a%20new%20currency%20while%20retaining%20the%20power%20and%20authority%20of%20the%20conventional%20social%20elites.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThough%20Ambedkar%20envisaged%20that%20the%20Dalit-Bahujan%20groups%20would%20utilise%20the%20ancient%20religious%20resources%20to%20counter%20the%20Brahmanical%20cultural%20hegemony%20effectively%2C%20it%20is%20the%20conventional%20social%20elites%20who%20have%20instrumentalised%20the%20Hindu%20religious%20and%20cultural%20symbols%20more%20effectively%2C%20including%20the%20appropriation%20of%20neo-Buddhism%20than%20the%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20established%20its%20permanency%20in%20the%20democratic%20discourse.%20Therefore%2C%20it%20is%20crucial%20to%20revisit%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20ideological%20and%20ethical%20values%20in%20such%20troubled%20times%20and%20to%20re-establish%20its%20relevance%20in%20transforming%20the%20corrupt%20social%20order%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20liberty%2C%20equality%2C%20and%20fraternity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fharish-s-wankhede%5C%22%3EHarish%20S.%20Wankhede%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20Assistant%20Professor%2C%20Center%20for%20Political%20Studies%2C%20School%20of%20Social%20Sciences%2C%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20University%2C%20New%20Delhi.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698141613000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F09%2F15105908%2Fambedkar-archival.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsociety%2Fhow-ambedkar-bridged-the-gap-between-religious-identity-and-western-modernity-through-buddhism%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22According%20to%20Ambedkar%2C%20Buddhism%20upholds%20humanism%2C%20individual%20freedom%2C%20and%20a%20peaceful%20coexistence%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20is%20suitable%20for%20the%20modern%20times.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A22%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsociety%2Fhow-ambedkar-bridged-the-gap-between-religious-identity-and-western-modernity-through-buddhism%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Freed%20Israeli%20hostage%20shown%20shaking%20hands%20with%20Hamas%20captor%20-%20before%20describing%20conditions%20she%20was%20kept%20in%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698139320000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F10%2F70x70%2Fskynews-sourasky-medical-center_6333460.jpg%3F20231024091027%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fisrael-gaza-war-freed-hostage-says-hamas-were-prepared-for-kidnappings-and-idf-did-not-take-warnings-seriously-12991386%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%2085-year-old%20hostage%20has%20been%20shown%20shaking%20hands%20with%20one%20of%20her%20Hamas%20captors%20as%20she%20was%20released.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A441%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fisrael-gaza-war-freed-hostage-says-hamas-were-prepared-for-kidnappings-and-idf-did-not-take-warnings-seriously-12991386%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fisrael-gaza-war-freed-hostage-says-hamas-were-prepared-for-kidnappings-and-idf-did-not-take-warnings-seriously-12991386%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fisrael-gaza-war-freed-hostage-says-hamas-were-prepared-for-kidnappings-and-idf-did-not-take-warnings-seriously-12991386%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22There%20May%20Be%20a%20Silver%20Lining%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20Marriage%20Equality%20Judgment%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F18190519%2FDelhi-Pride-Parade-LGBTQ-rights-13.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20recent%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scobserver.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2FJudgement-Plea-for-Marriage-Equality.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ejudgment%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20the%20Indian%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20marriage%20equality%20was%2C%20without%20a%20doubt%2C%20a%20disappointment%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20queer%20community.%20With%20a%203%3A2%20majority%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20held%20that%20queer%20couples%20in%20non-heterosexual%20relationships%20do%20not%20have%20a%20fundamental%20right%20to%20marry%20and%20denied%20legal%20recognition%20to%20their%20relationships.%20The%20court%E2%80%99s%20judgment%20placed%20heterosexuality%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20marital%20relationships%20by%20holding%20that%20marriage%20between%20persons%20of%20opposite%20gender%20is%20the%20only%20valid%20form%20of%20marriage%20under%20Indian%20law.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThus%2C%20while%20transgender%20persons%20identifying%20within%20the%20gender%20binary%20who%20are%20in%20heterosexual%20relationships%20are%20entitled%20to%20marry%2C%20queer%20couples%20who%20do%20not%20find%20themselves%20in%20what%20can%20be%20classified%20as%20heterosexual%20relationships%20are%20left%20without%20any%20legal%20remedy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20perhaps%20in%20rejecting%20that%20there%20is%20any%20fundamental%20right%20to%20marry%20under%20the%20Constitution%20for%20queer%20couples%20or%20otherwise%2C%20the%20court%20has%20opened%20a%20portal%20(especially%20in%20the%20minority%20opinions)%20for%20re-imagining%20the%20existence%20of%20what%20were%20understood%20to%20be%20matrimonial%20entitlements%20(like%20succession%20rights%2C%20adoption%2C%20guardianship%2C%20financial%20entitlements%20that%20accrue%20to%20spouses%20etc.)%20beyond%20marriage.%20We%20discuss%20the%20implications%20of%20this%20possibility.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20petitioners%20had%20primarily%20mounted%20a%20challenge%20to%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20Special%20Marriage%20Act%2C%201954%20arguing%20that%20the%20non-recognition%20of%20non-heterosexual%20marriages%20under%20the%20Act%20violated%20their%20fundamental%20right%20to%20marry%20and%20discriminated%20against%20them%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20sexual%20orientation.%20An%20important%20prong%20of%20the%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20argument%20was%20that%20they%20are%20denied%20the%20matrimonial%20benefits%20listed%20above.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Ftwo-steps-forward-three-steps-back-supreme-court-verdict-marriage-equality%5C%22%3ETwo%20Steps%20Forward%2C%20Three%20Steps%20Back%3A%20Supreme%20Court%20Verdict%20on%20Marriage%20Equality%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EMany%20challenge%20the%20idea%20of%20marriage%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98norm%E2%80%99%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndeed%2C%20the%20queer%20community%E2%80%99s%20quest%20for%20marriage%20is%20either%20grounded%20in%20(i)%20the%20belief%20that%20marriage%20is%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Enormative%20ideal%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eto%20which%20queer%20people%20should%20also%20have%20access%20to%3B%20or%20(ii)%20marriage%20provides%20a%20bouquet%20of%20entitlements%2C%20the%20absence%20of%20which%20significantly%20disadvantages%20those%20in%20queer%20relationships.%20Some%20queer%20individuals%20will%20agree%20with%20both%20propositions.%20But%20many%20challenge%20the%20elevation%20of%20marriage%20as%20the%20norm%20and%20as%20an%20ideal%20that%20all%20of%20us%20should%20aspire%20towards.%20They%20highlight%20the%20oppressive%20foundations%20of%20marriage%2C%20specifically%20its%20heterosexist%20nature%20and%20foundation%20in%20caste%20endogamy%2C%20which%20is%20difficult%20to%20dismantle.%20Further%2C%20they%20argue%20that%20marriage%20as%20an%20institution%2C%20through%20the%20bundle%20of%20rights%20and%20entitlements%20it%20provides%2C%20privileges%20married%20partners%20over%20others%20who%20choose%20to%20not%20marry%20or%20cannot%20marry.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20difficult%20to%20contest%20that%20marriage%20is%20founded%20on%20heterosexist%20norms.%20Marriage%20continues%20to%20be%20imagined%20primarily%20as%20a%20heterosexual%20union%20(even%20if%20the%20social%20reality%20may%20be%20different%20or%20is%20changing).%20Queer%20people%20across%20jurisdictions%20have%20won%20marriage%20rights%20after%20much%20suffering%20and%20only%20after%20being%20able%20to%20prove%20that%20their%20love%2Frelationship%20conforms%20to%20a%20heterosexual%20ideal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scobserver.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2FJudgement-Plea-for-Marriage-Equality-SR-Bhat-and-Hima-Kohli.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emajority%20opinion%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20authored%20by%20Justice%20Bhat%20in%20the%20marriage%20equality%20judgment%20also%20highlights%20and%20reinforces%20the%20heterosexist%20values%20that%20are%20attached%20to%20marriage.%20He%20says%2C%20%E2%80%98marriage%2C%20however%2C%20has%20been%20regarded%20for%20the%20longest%20time%2C%20as%20a%20relationship%20of%20man%20to%20woman%E2%80%99%20and%20at%20another%20place%2C%20he%20reiterates%20that%2C%20%E2%80%98traditions%20of%20marriage%20per%20se%20may%20not%20support%20the%20basis%20of%20recognition%20of%20marital%20relationships%20between%20non-heterosexual%20couples%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EExamples%20of%20weddings%20between%20same-sex%20couples%20in%20India%20or%20of%20relationships%20that%20are%20functionally%20identical%20to%20marriage%20between%20same-sex%20couples%20(in%20the%20absence%20of%20legal%20recognition)%20are%20not%20enough%20to%20displace%20the%20normative%20assumption%20that%20marriage%20is%20a%20heterosexual%20union.%20Social%20marriages%20that%20deviate%20from%20the%20heterosexual%20script%20are%20considered%20only%20as%20exceptions%2C%20not%20as%20evidence%20of%20a%20pluralist%20understanding%20of%20marriage.%20They%20remain%20exceptions%20because%20the%20norm%20that%20the%20marriage%20establishes%20is%20of%20the%20heterosexual%20union.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20if%20we%20say%20that%20queer%20couples%2C%20by%20gaining%20the%20legal%20right%20to%20marry%2C%20can%20somehow%20displace%20these%20heterosexist%20assumptions%20of%20who%20can%20marry%20and%20whom%2C%20they%20cannot%20dismantle%20the%20privilege%20of%20committed%20coupledom%20that%20marriage%20prescribes%20over%20other%20forms%20of%20adult%20associations%20and%20kinship.%20This%20is%20because%20these%20other%20forms%20of%20adult%20associations%20veer%20off%20the%20course%20of%20heteronormativity%20in%20ways%20that%20same-sex%20committed%20coupledom%20does%20not.%20As%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscholarship.law.columbia.edu%2Fbooks%2F10%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EKatherine%20Franke%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Ehas%20argued%3A%20same-sex%20marriage%20can%20still%20fall%20under%20the%20ambit%20of%20traditional%20family%20values%20that%20promote%20nuclear%20family%2C%20bourgeois%20respectability%20and%20privatised%20dependency.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EFeminist%20critique%20of%20marriage%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMarriage%E2%80%99s%20place%20as%20the%20normative%20ideal%20creates%20symbolic%20harm%20for%20individuals%2C%20queer%20or%20otherwise%2C%20who%20refuse%20to%20participate%20in%20marriage.%20In%20fact%2C%20feminist%20critiques%20of%20marriage%20as%20an%20oppressive%20institution%20have%20been%20the%20most%20trenchant.%20They%20have%20highlighted%20how%20marriage%20continues%20to%20be%20a%20patriarchal%20institution%2C%20even%20if%20many%20of%20the%20marriage%20laws%20that%20discriminated%20against%20women%20(like%20the%20law%20of%20coverture)%20have%20been%20removed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-courts-marriage-equality-judgment-represents-judicial-abdication%5C%22%3ESupreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20Marriage%20Equality%20Judgment%20Represents%20Judicial%20Abdication%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EQueer%20participation%20in%20marriage%20reinforces%20its%20status%20as%20the%20most%20sacred%20form%20of%20commitment%2C%20as%20the%20only%20relationship%20form%20that%20can%20confer%20dignity%20to%20queer%20lives%20and%20something%20that%20saves%20individuals%20from%20the%20doom%20of%20loneliness.%20In%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.law.cornell.edu%2Fsupct%2Fpdf%2F14-556.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EObergefell%20v.%20Hodges%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20relied%20on%20similar%20tropes%20stating%20that%20marriage%20has%20some%20transcendental%20importance%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20only%20institution%20that%20can%20fulfil%20our%20most%20%E2%80%98profound%20hopes%20and%20aspirations%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20Justice%20Bhat%20in%20the%20majority%20opinion%20refers%20to%20similar%20uncritical%20characterisations%20of%20marriage%2C%20stating%20that%20it%20is%20regarded%20%E2%80%98as%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20relationships%E2%80%99%20and%20a%20%E2%80%98building%20block%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20society.%20But%20do%20cohabiting%20unmarried%20partners%2C%20hijra%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Egharanas%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20mentors%20and%20mentees%20or%20intimate%20friends%20not%20form%20networks%20or%20relationships%20equally%20worthy%20as%20marriage%2C%20where%20they%20share%20love%2C%20caregiving%20responsibilities%20and%20companionship%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20marriage%20is%20an%20oppressive%20and%20exclusionary%20institution%20and%20queers%2C%20women%20and%20the%20unmarried%20are%20better%20off%20without%20it%2C%20at%20least%20its%20legal%20existence%2C%20why%20does%20it%20remain%20important%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20answer%20lies%20in%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scobserver.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2FJudgement-Plea-for-Marriage-Equality-CJI-Chandrachuds-Opinion.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eminority%20opinion%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20(CJI)%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20in%20the%20marriage%20equality%20judgment%20where%20he%20states%20that%20marriage%20is%20not%20by%20itself%20as%20fundamental%20to%20our%20lives%2C%20it%20has%20gained%20significance%20because%20the%20state%20regulation%20of%20%E2%80%98family%E2%80%99%20has%20conferred%20certain%20benefits%20to%20those%20who%20are%20married.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fglobal.oup.com%2Facademic%2Fproduct%2Fagainst-marriage-9780198845683%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EClare%20Chambers%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Enotes%2C%20marriage%20is%20the%20relationship%20that%20%E2%80%98the%20state%20assumes%2C%20defines%2C%20regulates%2C%20and%20recommends%E2%80%99.%20Hence%2C%20although%20marriage%20undermines%20our%20transformative%20goals%20of%20establishing%20an%20egalitarian%20order%20where%20a%20plurality%20and%20diversity%20of%20relationships%20or%20lifestyles%20are%20valued%2C%20we%20are%20forced%20to%20use%20the%20institution%20of%20marriage%20because%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20only%20way%20we%20get%20access%20to%20certain%20entitlements%20(next-of-kin%20privileges%2C%20ability%20to%20be%20on%20disability%20pension%20plans%20of%20our%20partners%2C%20employment%20benefits%2C%20workmen%E2%80%99s%20compensation%20etc.)%20These%20entitlements%20protect%20us%20from%20certain%20vulnerabilities%20that%20arise%20at%20the%20breakdown%20of%20relationships%20or%20our%20adult%20networks%20of%20care%20(through%20legal%20entitlements%20to%20shared%20property%2C%20custody%20of%20children%2C%20maintenance%20etc.)%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20creation%20of%20the%20concept%20of%20the%20right%20to%20form%20an%20abiding%20union%20(sans%20marriage)%20discussed%20in%20minority%20opinions%20of%20CJI%20Chandrachud%20and%20Justice%20Kaul%20goes%20someway%20in%20displacing%20the%20centrality%20of%20marriage%20over%20other%20relationship%20forms%20in%20our%20understanding%20of%20a%20family.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECJI%20Chandrachud%20in%20his%20minority%20opinion%20develops%20the%20concept%20of%20abiding%20cohabitational%20unions%20drawing%20from%20the%20observations%20in%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fpdf_upload%2F718-deepika-singh-v-central-administrative-tribunal-16-aug-2022-432626.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EDeepika%20Singh%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20judgment%20where%20he%20held%20that%20atypical%20families%20are%20equally%20deserving%20of%20protection%20under%20the%20law%20and%20benefits%20under%20the%20social%20welfare%20legislation%20as%20traditional%20families.%20In%20the%20marriage%20equality%20judgment%2C%20he%20emphasises%20that%20we%20may%20find%20%E2%80%98companionship%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98value-abiding%20relationships%20with%20other%20human%20beings%20in%20different%20forms%20and%20capacities%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fjustice-ravindra-bhat-marriage-equality-legacy-supreme-court%5C%22%3EJustice%20Ravindra%20Bhat%E2%80%99s%20Legacy%20Goes%20Beyond%20the%20%E2%80%98Marriage%20Equality%E2%80%99%20Judgment%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECJI%20Chandrachud%20finds%20the%20legal%20justification%20for%20the%20right%20to%20form%20such%20unions%20under%20Articles%2019%2C%2021%20and%2025%20of%20the%20constitution.%20Crucially%2C%20the%20CJI%20reads%20Article%2019(1)(c)%2C%20which%20confers%20the%20freedom%20of%20association%2C%20to%20include%20the%20right%20to%20form%20intimate%20associations.%20Now%20this%20has%20the%20possibility%20to%20extend%20beyond%20relations%20of%20conjugality%20or%20coupledom%20and%20encompass%20various%20permutations%20and%20combinations%2C%20even%20though%20CJI%20Chandrachud%20himself%20does%20not%20fully%20acknowledge%20this%20radical%20potential%20of%20the%20right%20to%20form%20intimate%20associations%20and%20limits%20himself%20to%20the%20discussion%20of%20queer%20couples%20forming%20unions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20is%20a%20certain%20tension%20in%20his%20opinion%20where%20he%20recognises%20that%20companionship%2C%20commitment%20and%20care%20can%20flow%20from%20different%20forms%20of%20associations%20%E2%80%93%20including%20friendship%2C%20mentor-mentee%20relationship%20or%20queer%20kinship%20networks%20that%20are%20not%20based%20on%20biological%20bonds%20%E2%80%93%20but%20then%20he%20reverts%20the%20idea%20of%20queer%20coupledom%20when%20he%20explicitly%20pens%20out%20who%20is%20the%20beneficiary%20of%20this%20right%20to%20form%20a%20union.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBe%20that%20as%20it%20may%20%E2%80%93%20and%20this%20is%20where%20the%20majority%20disagrees%20with%20him%20%E2%80%93%20CJI%20Chandrachud%2C%20says%20that%20these%20associations%20need%20to%20be%20recognised%20by%20the%20state%20so%20that%20there%20is%20actually%20a%20%E2%80%98free%20and%20unrestricted%E2%80%99%20exercise%20of%20this%20freedom.%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20the%20conditions%20that%20facilitate%20the%20exercise%20of%20a%20particular%20freedom%2C%20the%20freedom%20to%20do%20something%20becomes%20meaningless.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEntitlements%20such%20as%20access%20to%20ration%20cards%2C%20joint%20bank%20accounts%2C%20next-of-kin%20privileges%20in%20case%20of%20a%20medical%20event%2C%20jail%20visitation%20rights%2C%20access%20to%20the%20body%20on%20death%2C%20succession%20rights%2C%20maintenance%2C%20financial%20benefits%20under%20the%20Income%20Tax%20Act%20and%20employment%20benefits%20relating%20to%20gratuity%2C%20family%20pension%2C%20insurance%20etc.%20are%20usually%20exclusive%20to%20traditional%20families%20%E2%80%93%20relationships%20born%20out%20of%20marriage%20or%20blood%20ties.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECJI%20Chandrachud%20does%20not%20conclude%20that%20queer%20couples%20in%20unions%20are%20entitled%20to%20the%20same%20entitlements%20that%20a%20legally%20recognised%20married%20couple%20would%20possess%20but%20leaves%20it%20to%20a%20committee%20headed%20by%20the%20cabinet%20secretary%20to%20define%20and%20elucidate%20the%20scope%20of%20these%20entitlements.%20This%20deferral%20has%20been%20subject%20to%20criticism%20as%20the%20majority%20judgment%20refuses%20to%20even%20accord%20a%20right%20to%20union%20to%20queer%20couples%20and%20considering%20the%20position%20of%20the%20Union%20government%20on%20this%20issue%2C%20it%20is%20unlikely%20the%20executive%20would%20take%20on%20this%20task.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20many%20of%20the%20entitlements%20available%20to%20those%20in%20unions%20are%20left%20to%20the%20committee%20to%20decide%20on%2C%20the%20CJI%E2%80%99s%20minority%20opinion%20explicitly%20delinks%20adoption%20from%20marriage.%20Relying%20on%20Article%2014%20of%20the%20Constitution%20(right%20to%20equality)%20and%20Article%2015%20(right%20against%20discrimination)%2C%20he%20holds%20that%20both%20married%20and%20unmarried%20couples%20%E2%80%93%20including%20queer%20couples%20%E2%80%93%20are%20entitled%20to%20adopt.%20He%20questions%20the%20assumptions%20of%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20adoption%20regulations%20that%20envision%20that%20only%20married%20couples%20can%20provide%20a%20stable%20environment%20for%20a%20child.%20He%20observes%20that%20%E2%80%98there%20is%20no%20single%20form%20of%20a%20stable%20household%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECJI%20Chandrachud%20states%20the%20stability%20of%20a%20household%20is%20not%20dependent%20on%20marital%20status%20but%20rather%20on%20factors%20like%20the%20investment%20of%20time%20and%20effort%20by%20parents%20in%20running%20the%20household%2C%20their%20ability%20to%20create%20a%20safe%20space%2C%20the%20absence%20of%20physical%2C%20emotional%20and%20mental%20violence%20in%20the%20household%20etc.%20These%20observations%20displace%20marriage%20as%20the%20ideal%20and%20normative%20form%20of%20relationship.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20the%20majority%20opinion%2C%20in%20a%20disappointing%20turn%20of%20events%2C%20holds%20that%20while%20adoption%20law%20does%20make%20assumptions%20about%20who%20is%20fit%20to%20be%20a%20parent%2C%20there%20is%20once%20again%20a%20deference%20to%20the%20executive.%20In%20effect%2C%20the%20majority%20abdicated%20its%20responsibility%20for%20assessing%20the%20discriminatory%20assumptions%20that%20the%20law%20makes%20about%20unmarried%20couples%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20adoption.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EOther%20entitlements%20granted%20to%20%E2%80%98non-traditional%E2%80%99%20families%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20the%20right%20to%20adoption%2C%20the%20CJI%E2%80%99s%20opinion%20has%20fallen%20short%20of%20actually%20granting%20entitlements%20to%20non-traditional%20families.%20Both%20his%20and%20the%20majority%E2%80%99s%20opinion%20would%20have%20benefitted%20from%20looking%20at%20some%20of%20the%20other%20entitlements%20that%20have%20already%20been%20granted%20to%20non-traditional%20families.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Himachal%20Pradesh%20high%20court%20in%202016%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftranslaw.clpr.org.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F12%2FSweety_Eunuch_vs_General_Public_22062016__HPHCHP2016141016151351109COM53458.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Erecognised%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20customary%20significance%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Eguru-chela%3C%2Fem%3E%20relationship%20and%20held%20that%20the%20guru%20was%20entitled%20to%20the%20property%20of%20the%20deceased%20chela.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20Mental%20Healthcare%20Act%202017%20permits%20the%20nomination%20of%20a%20representative%20who%20does%20not%20fall%20within%20the%20traditional%20category%20of%20family.%20While%20these%20legal%20entitlements%20have%20limited%20import%2C%20the%20court%20had%20the%20opportunity%20to%20build%20upon%20these%20in%20the%20judgment%20to%20some%20extent%2C%20perhaps%20in%20the%20form%20of%20interim%20remedies%20instead%20of%20leaving%20the%20entire%20task%20to%20the%20executive.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOverall%2C%20we%20can%20derive%20two%20possibilities%20from%20CJI%20Chandrachud%E2%80%99s%20minority%20opinion%20for%20creating%20a%20more%20egalitarian%20legal%20framework%20on%20relationships%20i.e.%20(a)%20to%20think%20of%20intimate%20associations%20beyond%20marriage%20and%20(b)%20to%20delink%20what%20were%20thought%20to%20be%20matrimonial%20benefits%20from%20marriage.%20We%20note%20that%20the%20minority%20opinion%20of%20Chief%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20itself%20does%20not%20expand%20the%20concept%20of%20associations%20beyond%20coupledom%2C%20but%20it%20carries%20the%20radical%20potential%20to%20do%20so.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scobserver.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2FRituparna-Borah-and-Ors.-v.-UoI_Redacted.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ERituparna%20Borah%E2%80%99s%20petition%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20was%20one%20of%20the%20pleas%20filed%20in%20the%20marriage%20equality%20case%20that%20advocated%20for%20the%20queer%20individuals%E2%80%99%20right%20to%20form%20%E2%80%98chosen%20families%E2%80%99.%20The%20minority%20opinion%20creates%20an%20opening%20for%20demanding%20legal%20status%20and%20regulation%20for%20such%20%E2%80%98chosen%20families%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20different%20forms%20they%20may%20take.%20This%20can%20include%20creating%20legal%20access%20to%20material%20benefits%20as%20well%20as%20providing%20legal%20protection%20from%20vulnerabilities%20that%20arise%20on%20account%20of%20being%20in%20any%20relational%20setting.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20way%20forward%20for%20the%20queer%20community%2C%20perhaps%2C%20is%20not%20to%20insist%20on%20a%20right%20to%20marry%20but%20to%20challenge%20laws%20that%20privilege%20marriage%20over%20other%20forms%20of%20familial%20and%20kinship%20bonds.%20It%20is%20to%20return%20to%20the%20politics%20of%20queer%20liberation%20which%20has%20space%20for%20plurality%20and%20diversity.%20It%20is%20not%20to%20resign%20ourselves%20to%20a%20second-class%20status%20but%20to%20build%20coalitions%20with%20those%20who%20are%20perhaps%20not%20queer%20by%20identity%20but%20still%20%E2%80%98queer%E2%80%99%20enough%20to%20reject%20the%20institution%20of%20marriage.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20what%20of%20the%20majority%20opinion%20one%20may%20ask%3F%20While%20the%20majority%20has%20rejected%20the%20right%20to%20form%20a%20union%2C%20Article%2014%20(right%20to%20equality)%20which%20requires%20the%20state%20to%20make%20reasonable%20classification%20still%20exists.%20The%20classification%20between%20married%20and%20unmarried%20under%20the%20law%20is%20often%20more%20moral%20than%20reasonable.%20Also%2C%20many%20important%20constitutional%20principles%20that%20we%20know%20today%20found%20their%20place%20first%20in%20the%20dissents%20or%20minority%20opinions%2C%20before%20they%20became%20the%20opinions%20of%20the%20court.%20There%20is%20much%20to%20be%20discontented%20with%2C%20but%20transformative%20readings%20of%20law%20are%20always%20possible.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EAishwarya%20Singh%20is%20a%20lecturer%20at%20Jindal%20Global%20Law%20School%2C%20Sonipat.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EMeenakshi%20Ramkumar%20is%20a%20Visiting%20Assistant%20Professor%20at%20the%20National%20Law%20School%20of%20India%20University%2C%20Bangalore%20teaching%20Family%20Law.%20Views%20expressed%20are%20personal.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EDisclaimer%3A%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EAishwarya%20Singh%20is%20a%20former%20judicial%20law%20clerk%20of%20CJI%20Chandrachud.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698138059000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F18190519%2FDelhi-Pride-Parade-LGBTQ-rights-13.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthere-may-be-a-silver-lining-in-the-supreme-courts-marriage-equality-judgement%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20way%20forward%20for%20the%20queer%20community%2C%20perhaps%2C%20is%20not%20to%20insist%20on%20a%20right%20to%20marry%20but%20to%20challenge%20laws%20that%20privilege%20marriage%20over%20other%20forms%20of%20familial%20and%20kinship%20bonds.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthere-may-be-a-silver-lining-in-the-supreme-courts-marriage-equality-judgement%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%20to%20surpass%20Japan%2C%20be%20second%20largest%20Asian%20economy%20by%202030%3A%20S%26amp%3BP%20Global%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698137837000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-10%2F13%2Ffull%2F1697178838-2097.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Findia-to-surpass-japan-to-be-2nd-largest-eco-in-asia-by-2030-s-p-global-123102400344_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%2C%20the%20world's%20fifth%20largest%20economy%20in%20the%20world%2C%20is%20likely%20to%20overtake%20Japan%20to%20become%20the%20world's%20third-largest%20economy%20with%20a%20GDP%20of%20USD%207.3%20trillion%20b