en%20Hindus%20and%20Muslims%20are%20increasing%20in%20the%20country%2C%20but%20when%20I%20am%20in%20Bakshi%20Ka%20Talab%2C%20none%20of%20that%20hatred%20is%20perceptible.%20My%20family%20and%20the%20audience%20have%20been%20nothing%20but%20supportive%2C%20showering%20all%20their%20praise%20and%20encouragement%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Sahil%20Khan.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThousands%20of%20people%20gather%20to%20witness%20this%20unique%20Ramleela.%20Sanjeev%20Shukla%2C%2055%2C%20a%20resident%20of%20Bakshi%20Ka%20Talab%2C%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20I%20was%20a%20child%2C%20my%20father%20used%20to%20bring%20me%20to%20watch%20Ramleela.%20Now%20I%20bring%20my%20son%20to%20watch%20it.%20We%20feel%20a%20great%20sense%20of%20joy%20that%20our%20god%20is%20being%20respected%20and%20played%20by%20the%20people%20from%20other%20faiths%20also.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20director%20of%20this%20Ramleela%20is%20Mohammad%20Sabir%20Khan.%20He%20has%20been%20associated%20with%20it%20in%20various%20capacities%20for%2049%20years.%20He%20started%20directing%20Ramleela%20in%201990.%20%E2%80%9CAs%20a%20child%2C%20I%20used%20to%20watch%20Ramleela%20and%20longed%20to%20be%20part%20of%20it.%20Then%20I%20began%20this%20journey%20with%20the%20role%20of%20Jatayu%20and%20gradually%20started%20directing%20it.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F24112937%2Fimage-1421.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22940%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F24112937%2Fimage-1421.png%20940w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F24112937%2Fimage-1421-300x200.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-681496%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22626%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMohammad%20Sabir%20Khan.%20Photo%3A%20Aman%20Khan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20Sabir%20Khan%20shares%20insights%20with%20this%20scribe%2C%20rehearsals%20are%20underway.%20He%20advises%20Salman%20Khan%20that%20his%20facial%20expressions%20should%20reflect%20Lord%20Ram%E2%80%99s%20calm%20demeanor.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20was%20just%20one%20occasion%20when%20I%20encountered%20some%20objection%C2%A0%20to%20my%20participation%20in%20Ramleela.%20That%20was%20when%20I%20got%20married%2C%20and%20my%20in-laws%20raised%20concerns.%20I%20invited%20them%20to%20see%20our%20Ramleela%20first%20hand%2C%20and%20that%20became%20a%20turning%20point%20for%20them%20as%20they%20watched%20thousands%20of%20people%20applauding%20and%20praising%20my%20performance%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20Ramleela%20has%20seen%20many%20interesting%20phases.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EVidesh%20Pal%20Yadav%2C%20son%20of%20Maikulal%20Yadav%2C%20who%20was%20the%20founder%20member%20of%20Ramleela%20organising%20committee%2C%20shares%20an%20interesting%20anecdote.%20%E2%80%9COnce%2C%20Ramzaan%20(the%20holy%20month%20of%20fasting%20for%20Muslims)%20and%20Navratra%20(a%20Hindu%20festival)%20had%20coincided.%20We%20were%20worried%20about%20how%20we%20would%20manage%20Ramleela%20because%20most%20of%20our%20Muslim%20artists%20would%20be%20observing%20Roza%20(fasting)%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20recounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20none%20of%20them%20allowed%20their%20fasting%20to%20disrupt%20the%20smooth%20flow%20of%20the%20rehearsals.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9COn%20the%20final%20day%2C%20they%20%5Bthe%20artists%5D%20broke%20their%20fast%20(Iftaar)%20on%20the%20stage%20itself%2C%20just%20before%20starting%20the%20programme%20to%20ensure%20that%20there%20was%20no%20interruption%20in%20the%20performance.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20old%20connection%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20Lucknow%2C%20the%20tradition%20of%20a%20Muslim%20connection%20with%20Ramleela%20has%20deep%20roots.%20In%20the%201780s%2C%20Lucknow%E2%80%99s%20fourth%20nawab%2C%20Asaf-ud-Daula%2C%20donated%206%20acres%20of%20land%20to%20establish%20a%20Ramleela%20ground%20in%20the%20Aishbagh%20locality%2C%20where%20the%20annual%20Ramleela%20has%20been%20held%20ever%20since.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Aditya%20Dwivedi%2C%20secretary%20of%20the%20Aishbagh%20Ramleela%20Samiti%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20renowned%20Ramleela%20in%20India.%20It%20was%20started%20by%20Goswami%20Tulsidas%20in%20the%2016th%20century.%20In%20the%20beginning%2C%20Sadhus%20used%20to%20perform%20Ramleela%20here.%20However%2C%20during%20the%20era%20of%20the%20Nawabs%2C%20many%20Nawabs%20began%20attending%20Ramleela%2C%20and%20they%20were%20so%20fond%20of%20it%20that%20they%20used%20to%20take%20care%20of%20the%20expenses.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEven%20today%2C%20many%20Muslims%20actively%20participate%20in%20the%20Aishbagh%20Ramleela.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F24114245%2Fimage-1422.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22940%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F24114245%2Fimage-1422.png%20940w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F24114245%2Fimage-1422-300x200.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-681498%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22626%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAishbagh%20Ramleela.%20Photo%3A%20Aman%20Khan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3ESyed%20Shamshur%20Rahman%20Naved%20has%20been%20the%20dance%20director%20of%20the%20Aishbagh%20Ramleela%20since%202006.%20He%20is%20responsible%20for%20choreographing%20the%20dance%20sequences%20throughout%20the%2010-day-long%20ritual.%3C%2F