Despite%20Handsome%20Hike%20in%20MSP%20for%20Wheat%2C%20Challenges%20Remain%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F19114936%2F2803401637_c66168e706_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20has%20announced%20a%207.1%25%20increase%20in%20the%20MSP%20of%20wheat%20for%20the%20rabi%20crop%20(Rs%202%2C275%20per%20quintal)%2C%20for%20which%20sowing%20is%20just%20beginning.%20This%20is%20the%20highest%20rate%20of%20increase%20in%20the%20last%2010%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWheat%20is%20the%20largest%20rabi%20crop%20and%20only%20a%20few%20years%20back%2C%20commentators%2C%20including%20this%20writer%2C%20were%20looking%20for%20ways%20to%20reduce%20the%20procurement%20of%20wheat%20at%20MSP%20because%20the%20government%20was%20procuring%20much%20more%20than%20its%20requirement%20for%20meeting%20its%20obligations%20under%20the%20National%20Food%20Security%20Act%2C%20welfare%20schemes%20and%20the%20Open%20Market%20Sale%20Scheme%20(OMSS).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20what%20has%20changed%20in%20just%20over%20four%20years%3F%20The%20answer%20is%3A%20weather.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGovernment%20data%20of%20production%20does%20not%20show%20any%20significant%20decrease.%20The%20estimate%20of%20wheat%20production%20(issued%20in%20May%202023)%20for%202021-22%20and%202022-23%20was%20107.74%20million%20tonnes%20(mt)%20and%20112.74%20mt%20respectively.%20The%20trade%20estimates%20(unverified)%20were%2C%20however%2C%20lower%20by%20about%202-5%20mt.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20final%20estimate%20for%202022-23%20released%20on%20October%2018%2C%202023%2C%20the%20government%20has%20acknowledged%20that%20wheat%20production%20was%20lower%2C%20at%20110.55%20mt.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20wheat%20prices%20in%20the%20open%20market%20had%20been%20rising.%20In%20January%202023%2C%20wheat%20inflation%20reached%2025%25%20and%20mandi%20prices%20were%20hovering%20around%20Rs%202%2C700-2800%20per%20quintal.%20The%20MSP%20for%20the%20Rabi%20Marketing%20Season%20(RMS)%202023-24%2C%20beginning%20in%20April%2C%20was%20only%20Rs%202%2C125%20per%20quintal.%20To%20bring%20down%20wheat%20prices%20to%20the%20level%20of%20MSP%20so%20that%20the%20government%20can%20procure%2C%20it%20sold%203.3%20mt%20of%20wheat%20under%20OMSS%20in%20February%20and%20March%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWheat%20prices%20in%20mandis%20did%20come%20down%20and%20the%20government%20procured%2026.2%20mt%20in%20RMS%202023-24.%20In%20the%20previous%20year%2C%20the%20government%20had%20procured%20only%2018.8%20mt%20of%20wheat.%20This%20was%20just%20about%20sufficient%20to%20meet%20its%20requirements%20for%20NFSA%2C%20welfare%20schemes%20and%20OMSS.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20would%20not%20like%20the%20story%20to%20be%20repeated%20this%20year%2C%20so%20a%207.1%25%20increase%20in%20MSP%20of%20wheat%20is%20neither%20surprising%20nor%20imprudent.%20It%20is%20not%20that%20the%20government%20has%20been%20unaware%20of%20the%20emerging%20threat%20of%20adverse%20weather%20events.%20With%20more%20resources%20at%20its%20command%20than%20anyone%20else%2C%20the%20government%20has%20a%20more%20accurate%20understanding%20of%20market%20trends%20of%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20early%20as%20August%2016%2C%202021%2C%20the%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Board%20of%20India%20(SEBI)%20suspended%20the%20launch%20of%20any%20new%20contract%20of%20chana%20on%20the%20National%20Commodity%20and%20Derivatives%20Exchange%20(NCDEX).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20December%2020%2C%202021%2C%20SEBI%20banned%20futures%20and%20options%20contracts%20in%20seven%20agricultural%20commodities%20for%20one%20year%2C%20that%20is%2C%20till%20December%2020%2C%202022.%20The%20ban%20was%20applicable%20to%20wheat%2C%20paddy%20(non-basmati)%2C%20chana%2C%20mustard%20seeds%20and%20their%20derivatives%2C%20soyabean%2C%20crude%20palm%20oil%20and%20moong.%20It%20has%20been%20extended%20till%20December%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20market%20prices%20of%20several%20of%20the%20banned%20commodities%20have%20stayed%20mostly%20below%20MSP.%20Yet%20the%20ban%20on%20future%20trading%20continues%20and%20NCDEX%2C%20the%20largest%20exchange%2C%20may%20be%20facing%20huge%20losses.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20experts%20were%20talking%20about%20India%20becoming%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2Fee27db1a-cabb-400c-92e6-281cbec51a12%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoiaHpuMnUifQ.MQOquijPBw98XVYBc9m195DW7Qx9ruSvngQYE7EwHGg%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2Fee27db1a-cabb-400c-92e6-281cbec51a12%3Fj%253DeyJ1IjoiaHpuMnUifQ.MQOquijPBw98XVYBc9m195DW7Qx9ruSvngQYE7EwHGg%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1698201646570000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw0W9b3e4nKdvaL416xTLK6z%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epermanent%20agriculturally%20surplus%20nation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20government%20has%20used%20all%20the%20measures%20at%20its%20command%20to%20rein%20in%20food%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20like%20to%20procure%20at%20least%2025-30%20million%20tonnes%20of%20wheat%20from%20the%20rabi%20crop%20of%202023-24%20(in%20the%20RMS%202024-25%20beginning%20from%20April%202024).%20An%20attractive%20MSP%20was%20therefore%20necessary%20to%20bring%20farmers%20to%20the%20procurement%20centres%20of%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20has%20already%20taken%20strong%20action%20to%20contain%20domestic%20prices%20of%20wheat.%20In%20May%202022%2C%20export%20of%20wheat%20was%20banned.%20In%20August%202022%2C%20the%20export%20of%20wheat%20atta%20and%20products%20was%20also%20banned.%20In%20June%202023%2C%20stockholding%20limits%20were%20imposed%20on%20wheat%20and%20retailers%20are%20not%20allowed%20now%20to%20hold%20more%20than%2010%20tonnes%20at%20each%20retail%20outlet.%20Even%20big%20chain%20retailers%20can%20keep%20only%20up%20to%2010%20tonnes%20at%20each%20outlet%20and%203%2C000%20tonnes%20at%20all%20their%20depots%20combined.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20at%20the%20peak%20of%20the%20festival%20season%2C%20and%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2F980a2fce-ab97-4356-9322-27bede5bf367%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoiaHpuMnUifQ.MQOquijPBw98XVYBc9m195DW7Qx9ruSvngQYE7EwHGg%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2F980a2fce-ab97-4356-9322-27bede5bf367%3Fj%253DeyJ1IjoiaHpuMnUifQ.MQOquijPBw98XVYBc9m195DW7Qx9ruSvngQYE7EwHGg%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1698201646570000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw3sxDYYOMpqPxo0WMOr_Wou%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emarket%20prices%20of%20wheat%20have%20touched%20Rs%2027%2C390%20per%20quintal%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20Delhi.%20The%20import%20duty%20on%20wheat%20is%2040%25.%20If%20it%20is%20lowered%2C%20the%20private%20sector%20could%20find%20parity%20to%20import%20it%20at%20southern%20ports.%20This%20could%20cool%20down%20the%20prices%20of%20wheat.%20And%20it%20would%20also%20have%20an%20impact%20on%20prices%20of%20other%20essential%20commodities%20which%20tend%20to%20rise%20in%20sympathy%20with%20wheat.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20seems%20that%20adverse%20weather%20events%20have%20had%20a%20deep%20impact%20on%20India%E2%80%99s%20agricultural%20success.%20Much%20higher%20investment%20in%20research%20is%20needed%20to%20develop%20climate-resistant%20varieties%20of%20seeds%2C%20as%20a%20matter%20of%20priority.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESiraj%20Hussain%20is%20a%20former%20Union%20Agriculture%20Secretary.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698129020000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F19114936%2F2803401637_c66168e706_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fdespite-handsome-hike-in-msp-for-wheat-challenges-remain%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20seems%20that%20adverse%20weather%20events%20have%20had%20a%20deep%20impa