%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20arm%20the%20refugees%20from%20Myanmar%20but%20we%20simply%20provide%20them%20food%20and%20shelter%20on%20humanitarian%20grounds%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELast%20month%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmizroam-to-ignore-centres-order-to-collect-biometric-data-of-refugees-from-myanmar%5C%22%3EZoramthanga%20had%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20his%20government%20would%20not%20be%20following%20the%20Union%20home%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20directive%20to%20collect%20biometric%20data%20from%20refugees.%20%E2%80%9CCollection%20of%20biometric%20and%20biographic%20data%20of%20Myanmar%20refugees%20would%20amount%20to%20discrimination%20against%20people%20who%20are%20of%20our%20blood%20and%20kindred%20brothers%20and%20sisters.%20Keeping%20this%20in%20mind%2C%20it%20was%20decided%20not%20to%20undertake%20this%20as%20of%20now%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fzoramthanga-on-ucc-and-manipur-violence%5C%22%3Espoken%20out%20against%3C%2Fa%3E%20plans%20for%20a%20Uniform%20Civil%20Code%2C%20which%20several%20BJP%20leaders%20have%20been%20pushing.%20He%20has%20also%20raised%20his%20voice%20on%20the%20ethnic%20violence%20in%20Manipur%20several%20times%2C%20which%20the%20state%20and%20Union%20BJP%20governments%20have%20been%20accused%20of%20mishandling.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698121446000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29124850%2FF05qfKDacAAHNnr.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fciting-burnt-churches-in-manipur-mizoram-cm-says-wont-share-campaign-stage-with-modi%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BTo%20have%20sympathy%20with%20the%20BJP%20at%20this%20time%20will%20be%20a%20big%20minus%20point%20for%20my%20point%20for%20my%20party%2C%26quot%3B%20Zoramthanga%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A73%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fciting-burnt-churches-in-manipur-mizoram-cm-says-wont-share-campaign-stage-with-modi%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20Does%20it%20Mean%2C%20Today%2C%20to%20Be%20'With%20Israel'%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F24091521%2Fchurch-of-the-holy-sepulchre-9292.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20with%20Israel.%E2%80%9D%20What%20is%20the%20meaning%20of%20this%20assertion%3F%20And%20can%20anyone%20deny%20this%3F%20What%20is%20a%20country%20but%20its%20people%3F%20Why%20should%20anyone%20have%20any%20hesitation%20in%20being%20with%20any%20people%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20being%20with%20Israel%20today%20means%20being%20against%20Palestine.%20It%20has%20been%20accepted%20that%20the%20slogan%20%E2%80%98Long%20live%20Israel%E2%80%99%20will%20mean%20%E2%80%98Down%20with%20Palestine%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20also%20a%20strange%20thing%20that%20today%20all%20over%20the%20world%2C%20be%20it%20France%20or%20England%2C%20the%20US%20or%20Germany%2C%20Turkey%20or%20Africa%2C%20streets%20are%20reverberating%20with%20slogans%20like%20%E2%80%98We%20are%20Palestine%E2%80%99.%20Thousands%20and%20lakhs%20of%20people%20in%20these%20countries%20are%20holding%20the%20Palestinian%20flag.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20governments%20of%20these%20countries%20are%20hoisting%20the%20Israeli%20flag%20on%20their%20buildings.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20governments%20are%20threatening%20those%20who%20utter%20the%20word%20Palestine%20with%20punishment.%20But%20their%20people%20are%20thumbing%20their%20noses%20at%20this%20threat%20and%20raising%20slogans%20on%20the%20streets%3A%20%E2%80%98From%20river%20to%20the%20sea%2C%20Palestine%20will%20be%20free.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EObjection%20has%20been%20raised%20to%20this%20slogan%20in%20England.%20The%20meaning%20of%20this%20slogan%20is%20the%20denial%20of%20the%20existence%20of%20Israel%2C%20this%20is%20the%20allegation.%20People%20participating%20in%20the%20procession%20said%2C%20when%20we%20raise%20this%20slogan%2C%20we%20do%20not%20talk%20about%20destroying%20Israel%2C%20we%20only%20demand%20the%20freedom%20of%20Palestine.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%20one%20had%20to%20choose%20between%20these%20two%2C%20what%20would%20one%20choose%3F%20Does%20the%20flag%20of%20a%20country%20look%20good%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20people%20or%20in%20government%20offices%3F%20What%20would%20the%20people%20of%20Israel%20themselves%20feel%3F%20Do%20they%20consider%20it%20a%20matter%20of%20pride%20that%20the%20unarmed%20people%20across%20the%20world%20have%20the%20flag%20of%20Palestine%20in%20their%20hands%20and%20the%20anthem%20of%20Palestine%20on%20their%20lips%20but%20Israel%20exists%20only%20in%20the%20statements%20of%20armed%20governments%3F%20Which%20one%20of%20the%20two%20should%20be%20a%20matter%20of%20pride%20for%20any%20people%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHow%20would%20the%20people%20of%20Israel%20feel%20seeing%20the%20colours%20of%20Palestine%20on%20the%20streets%20around%20the%20world%3F%20Would%20they%20be%20feeling%20lonely%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22The%20First%20Sights%20and%20Sounds%20of%20War%3A%20Notes%20from%20Israel-Palestine%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fisrael-diary-gaza-occupation%5C%22%3EThe%20First%20Sights%20and%20Sounds%20of%20War%3A%20Notes%20from%20Israel-Palestine%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20one%20who%20is%20with%20Palestine%20should%20probably%20say%20that%20he%20is%20with%20Israel%20also.%20The%20right%20to%20life%20of%20these%20two%20people%20are%20not%20and%20should%20not%20be%20mutually%20exclusive.%20Which%20means%20the%20right%20to%20live%20with%20dignity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20Palestinians%20do%20not%20have%20dignity%2C%20the%20Israelis%20feel%20insecure%20because%20it%20is%20in%20their%20name%20that%20the%20Palestinians%20have%20been%20robbed%20of%20their%20dignity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%20what%20does%20it%20mean%20to%20be%20with%20Israel%3F%20Who%20is%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20well-wisher%20at%20this%20time%3F%20The%20one%20that%20is%20pushing%20Israel%20deeper%20into%20the%20closed%20tunnel%20of%20war%20and%20violence%3F%20Or%20the%20one%20who%20is%20warning%20it%20that%20this%20tunnel%20is%20closed%20from%20the%20front%20and%20entering%20it%20means%20being%20trapped%20in%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWho%20is%20really%20with%20Israel%3F%20All%20those%20people%20who%20echo%20the%20Israeli%20government%E2%80%99s%20shout%20for%20revenge%20for%20the%20October%207%20Hamas%20attack%3F%20Those%20who%20support%20or%20are%20silent%20after%20the%20Israeli%20government%20murdered%20more%20than%204%2C500%20people%20in%20Gaza%20and%20pulverised%20it%3F%20Or%20those%20who%20are%20still%20saying%20that%20the%20answer%20to%20the%20Hamas%20attack%20is%20not%20to%20destroy%20Gaza%3F%20They%20ask%20Israel%20not%20be%20hotheaded%20as%20it%20has%20always%20been%2C%20and%20use%20this%20opportunity%20with%20a%20cool%20mind%20to%20get%20out%20of%20the%20vicious%20cycle%20of%20violence%20in%20which%20Israel%20has%20put%20itself%20and%20the%20Palestinians%20along%20with%20it%20for%20the%20last%2075%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%20are%20all%20those%20people%20and%20their%20leaders%20like%20Joe%20Biden%20and%20Rishi%20Sunak%2C%20who%20came%20running%20to%20embrace%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20criminal%20thoroughly%20discredited%20and%20war%20hungry%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%2C%20well-wishers%20of%20the%20people%20of%20Israel%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIs%20their%20priority%20the%20release%20of%20more%20than%20200%20people%20held%20hostage%20by%20Hamas%3F%20When%20the%20Israeli%20government%20started%20bombing%20Gaza%2C%20did%20it%20have%20these%20people%2C%20its%20own%20people%20in%20mind%2C%20who%20could%20be%20killed%20in%20this%20bombing%3F%20Instead%20of%20this%20bombing%2C%20would%20it%20not%20have%20been%20better%20to%20find%20a%20way%20to%20negotiate%20with%20Hamas%20and%20first%20free%20these%20hostages%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBe%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.haaretz.com%2Fopinion%2F2023-10-10%2Fty-article%2F.premium%2Farriving-again-at-the-cycle-of-vengeance%2F0000018b-15d7-d2fc-a59f-d5df4d810000%5C%22%3EAmira%20Hass%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fvideo-gideon-levy-karan-thapar-gaza-israel-palestine%5C%22%3EGideon%20Levy%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nybooks.com%2Fonline%2F2023%2F10%2F11%2Fdeja-vu-in-israel%2F%5C%22%3EDavid%20Shulma%3C%2Fa%3En%2C%20hundreds%2C%20thousands%20of%20Israelis%20are%20shouting%20that%20if%20Israel%20wants%20a%20life%20of%20peace%20then%20it%20will%20have%20to%20liberate%20Palestine.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIsrael%E2%80%99s%20former%20advisor%20Daniel%20Levy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fprogram%2Fthe-bottom-line%2F2023%2F10%2F21%2Fwhy-does-the-us-not-support-a-ceasefire-in-gaza%5C%22%3Esaid%20in%20his%20interview%20to%20%3Cem%3EAl%20Jazeera%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20before%20condemning%20the%20attack%20by%20Hamas%2C%20there%20is%20a%20need%20to%20ask%20the%20fundamental%20question%2C%20how%20did%20we%20all%20reach%20this%20point%3F%20Why%20are%20we%20forced%20to%20ask%20this%20question%3F%20Levy%20said%20that%20the%20need%20to%20ask%20this%20question%20would%20not%20arise%20if%20millions%20of%20Palestinians%20had%20not%20been%20crushed%20every%20day%20for%2075%20years%20in%20a%20tight%20space%20in%20one%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20most%20cruel%20prisons.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20is%20not%20why%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20intelligence%20system%20failed%20and%20why%20it%20was%20not%20even%20aware%20of%20such%20long%20preparations%20by%20Hamas.%20The%20real%20question%20is%20who%20made%20Hamas%20powerful%3F%20Why%20did%20Israeli%20governments%2C%20and%20Netanyahu%20in%20particular%2C%20pit%20Hamas%20against%20Fatah%3F%20Why%20did%20Israel%20refuse%20to%20honour%20even%20the%20Oslo%20Agreement%2C%20and%20why%20did%20it%20continue%20to%20steal%20Palestinian%20land%20under%20the%20watchful%20eye%20of%20the%20US%2C%20continue%20killing%20Palestinians%20and%20humiliating%20them%20on%20an%20hourly%20basis%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%2C%20who%20created%20such%20a%20situation%20that%20Israel%20has%20to%20see%20Hamas%20in%20every%20Palestinian%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDaniel%20Levy%20cautions%20that%20even%20after%20razing%20Gaza%2C%20Israel%20will%20never%20have%20more%20security%20than%20it%20has%20today.%20The%20only%20guarantee%20of%20the%20security%20of%20the%20people%20of%20Israel%20is%20a%20free%20Palestine.%20When%20you%20suppress%20someone%2C%20you%20have%20to%20keep%20increasing%20that%20pressure%20because%20the%20desire%20of%20the%20person%20being%20suppressed%20to%20raise%20his%20head%20increases%20in%20the%20same%20proportion.%20Then%20you%20are%20always%20alert%2C%20putting%20a%20lot%20of%20your%20energy%20into%20increasing%20that%20pressure%20to%20keep%20him%20under%20your%20boot.%20It%E2%80%99s%20better%20to%20get%20off%20his%20back%20and%20let%20him%20walk%20straight.%20Then%20you%20too%20will%20be%20able%20to%20walk%20peacefully%20next%20to%20him.%20It%20is%20just%20that%20simple.%20If%20Israel%20wants%20peace%20then%20it%20will%20have%20to%20give%20freedom%20to%20the%20Palestinians.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EApoorvanand%20teaches%20at%20Delhi%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698119189000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F24091521%2Fchurch-of-the-holy-sepulchre-9292.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fwhat-does-it-mean-today-to-be-with-israel%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22If%20Israel%20wants%20peace%20then%20it%20will%20have%20to%20give%20freedom%20to%20the%20Palestinians.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A37%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fwhat-does-it-mean-today-to-be-with-israel%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bishan%20Singh%20Bedi%20Bowled%20to%20Deceive%20but%2C%20Frank%20and%20Big-Hearted%2C%20Was%20the%20Least%20Deceptive%20of%20Men%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F24083056%2FF9Hm3y3W0AAny2G.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20certain%20genus%20of%20cricketers%20%E2%80%93%20an%20elite%20of%20the%20elite%20%E2%80%93%20who%20are%20not%20only%20supreme%20at%20their%20skill%20but%20somehow%20seem%20to%20embody%20it%20altogether.%20Shane%20Warne%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20just%20leg%20spin%E2%80%99s%20greatest%20exponent%3B%20to%20bowling%2C%20he%20somehow%20brought%20the%20full%20force%20of%20his%20vibrant%20personality.%20Wasim%20Akram%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20merely%20the%20left-arm%20pace%20bowler%20supreme%2C%20but%20an%20encyclopedist%20of%20the%20craft%2C%20the%20master%20of%20all%20its%20aspects%20and%20dimensions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBishan%20Singh%20Bedi%20formed%20part%20of%20this%20club.%20He%20was%20left-arm%20slow%20bowling.%20He%20was%20its%20greatest%20champion%20and%20its%20most%20joyous%20ambassador.%20He%20bowled%20it%20on%20the%20field%3B%20he%20bowled%20it%20in%20his%20head%3B%20he%20bowled%20it%20into%20eternity.%20Once%20you%20saw%20him%2C%20he%20became%20the%20benchmark%2C%20the%20reference%20point%20for%20all%20other%20practitioners.%20He%20wakened%20you%20to%20its%20possibilities%2C%20and%20once%20wakened%20you%20never%20forgot%20them.%20More%20than%2040%20years%20have%20elapsed%20since%20he%20bowled%2C%20but%20he%20led%20me%20on%20to%20other%20favourites%20like%20Ravi%20Shastri%2C%20Daniel%20Vettori%20and%20Rangana%20Herath%2C%20and%20I%20fancy%20I%20still%20see%20him%20when%20I%20watch%20Ravi%20Jadeja%2C%20or%20Mitchell%20Santner.%20He%20also%20brought%20a%20unique%20spirit%20to%20cricket%20%E2%80%93%20an%20expansiveness%20and%20chivalry.%20He%20bowled%20to%20deceive%20but%2C%20frank%20and%20big-hearted%2C%20was%20the%20least%20deceptive%20of%20men.%20To%20face%20him%20must%20have%20been%20like%20having%20your%20pocket%20picked%20then%20being%20given%20your%20wallet%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThree%20times%20did%20Bishan%20tour%20Australia%3A%20as%20a%20young%20man%20in%201967-68%2C%20as%20a%20colourful%20guest%20in%20the%20Rest%20of%20the%20World%20XI%20in%201971-2%2C%20and%20as%20captain%20and%20guru%20in%201977-78.%20On%20that%20last%20trip%2C%20Indian%20brought%20their%20fabled%20four%20spinners%2C%20as%20complete%20an%20ensemble%20as%20has%20equipped%20any%20team%3A%20not%20just%20their%20skipper%20but%20gnomic%20Prasanna%2C%20crafty%20Venkat%2C%20and%20Chandra%2C%20sui%20generis.%20We%20tend%20to%20remember%20that%20Chandra%20took%2012%20on%20a%20dark%2C%20pebbly%20pitch%20at%20the%20MCG%2C%20but%20Bishan%20also%20took%2012%E2%80%A6in%20Perth%E2%80%A6at%20the%20WACA.%20Can%20you%20credit%20it%3F%20The%20world%E2%80%99s%20slowest%20bowler%20on%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20fastest%20pitch%20in%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20breeziest%20ground.%20To%20a%20boy%2C%20as%20I%20was%2C%20this%20was%20a%20kind%20of%20revelation%3A%20how%20much%20subtlety%20and%20variety%20could%20be%20wrung%20from%20a%20physique%20that%20testified%20to%20an%20enjoyment%20of%20earthy%20pleasures%2C%20an%20approach%20so%20seemingly%20artless%2C%20and%20an%20arc%20like%20an%20angler%E2%80%99s%20cast.%20It%20was%20intensified%20by%20Bishan%E2%80%99s%20seeming%20indifference%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20cricket.%20He%20hoicked%20earthily%3B%20he%20treated%20fielding%20as%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20chore.%20But%20in%20an%20over%20of%20Bishan%E2%80%99s%2C%20he%20made%20the%20world%20stand%20still%2C%20almost%20on%20tip-toe.%20The%20ball%20took%20so%20long%20in%20its%20path%2C%20time%20enough%20for%20thoughts%20to%20rush%20through%20a%20batter%E2%80%99s%20head%3B%20yet%20it%20was%20almost%20always%20a%20cardinal%20error%20to%20commit%20too%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBeaten%20in%20two%20squeakers%2C%20India%20just%20lost%20that%20series%20%E2%80%93%20imagine%20had%20they%20pulled%20it%20off%2C%20more%20than%2040%20years%20before%20Virat%20Kohli%E2%80%99s%20men%20of%202018-19.%20Remarkably%2C%20perhaps%2C%20I%20suspect%20that%20few%20Australians%20would%20have%20begrudged%20them.%20More%20powerful%20teams%20have%20visited%20our%20shores%2C%20but%20none%20so%20completely%20charming%3A%20valiant%20Mohinder%2C%20soulful%20Vishwanath%2C%20suave%20Vengsarkar%2C%20loveable%20Kirmani.%20It%20is%20incredible%20to%20think%20how%20long%20they%20stayed%2C%20all%20summer%2C%20and%20how%20far%20they%20travelled%2C%20through%20Mt%20Gambier.%20They%20came%20to%20my%20home%20town%2C%20a%20white%20bread%20industrial%20city%20called%20Geelong%2C%20where%20they%20trussed%20up%20the%20local%20XI.%20They%20felt%20like%20part%20of%20us%2C%20fascinating%20house%20guests%2C%20whom%20you%E2%80%99d%20have%20been%20happy%20to%20stay%20forever.%20Who%20of%20us%20in%20Australia%20had%20ever%20seen%20a%20patka%20before%2C%20such%20as%20those%20Bishan%20coiled%20around%20his%20head%3F%20Mind%20you%2C%20he%20could%20have%20bowled%20in%20a%20trilby%20and%20been%20just%20as%20entrancing.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20no%20fluke%2C%20I%20think%2C%20that%20Bishan%20is%20the%20subject%20of%20some%20of%20cricket%E2%80%99s%20best%20photographs.%20There%20was%20a%20feeling%20of%20a%20mystery%20to%20be%20unlocked%2C%20if%20you%20could%20just%20stop%20time%20long%20enough%20to%20study%20closely.%20There%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.espncricinfo.com%2Fphoto%2Fbishen-bedi-photographed-by-ken-kelly-in-1974-234198%3FobjectId%3D26875%5C%22%3EKen%20Kelly%E2%80%99s%20vivid%20close-up%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20the%20signature%20detail%20of%20Bishan%20imparting%20to%20the%20ball%20with%20his%20right%20thumb%20a%20last%20unconscious%20nudge%20into%20his%20left%20hand.%20There%E2%80%99s%20Adrian%20Murrell%E2%80%99s%20study%20of%20him%20warming%20up%2C%20only%20the%20whites%20of%20his%20eyes%20visible%2C%20as%20though%20lost%20in%20tantric%20contemplation.%20There%E2%80%99s%20Patrick%20Eagar%E2%80%99s%20side-on%20snap%20at%20Lord%E2%80%99s%20which%20captures%20Bedi%20connected%20to%20the%20ground%20only%20by%20the%20outside%20of%20the%20toe%20of%20his%20left%20boot%2C%20like%20a%20hot%20air%20balloon%20straining%20at%20its%20moorings.%20Seeing%20an%20Eagar%20sequence%20of%20Bedi%20in%20a%20copy%20of%20MCC%20Masterclass%20so%20inspired%20another%20young%20Sikh%2C%20Monty%20Panesar%2C%20that%20he%20committed%20to%20a%20lifetime%20in%20the%20same%20genre.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F24083208%2FF9JMon9WoAAF2wq.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22640%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F24083208%2FF9JMon9WoAAF2wq.jpeg%20640w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F24083208%2FF9JMon9WoAAF2wq-300x225.jpeg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-681470%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EBishan%20Singh%20Bedi.%20Photo%3A%20Shared%20on%20X%20by%20%40SonuSood%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3ESomething%20about%20the%20very%20memory%20of%20Bishan%20pricks%20you%20about%20directions%20the%20game%20has%20taken.%20Can%20you%20conceive%20of%20him%20in%20an%20auction%3F%20He%20was%20not%20to%20be%20bought%20and%20sold.%20Can%20you%20imagine%20the%20fatuity%20of%20putting%20a%20number%20and%20his%20name%20on%20the%20back%20of%20his%20shirt%3F%20It%20would%20have%20been%20like%20an%20explanatory%20caption%20on%20the%20Mona%20Lisa.%20He%20also%20belonged%20also%20to%20a%20now-forgotten%20species%20of%20cricketers%20%E2%80%93%20those%20rebel%20souls%20of%20the%201970s%20who%20were%20often%20at%20loggerheads%20with%20their%20administrative%20classes.%20Bishan%20was%20the%20Indian%20counterpart%20of%20Ian%20Chappell%20and%20Dennis%20Lillee%20in%20Australia%20and%20John%20Snow%20and%20Tony%20Greig%20in%20England.%20Today%E2%80%99s%20cricketers%2C%20memorable%20and%20exciting%20as%20they%20may%20be%2C%20are%20in%20the%20main%20pampered%20yes%20men%2C%20who%20never%20speak%20out%20of%20turn%2C%20lest%20they%20upset%20a%20brand%2C%20roil%20social%20media.%20They%20are%20represented%20by%20agents%20and%20unions%2C%20firewalled%20by%20entourages.%20Imagine%20the%20courage%20it%20once%20took%20to%20resist%20cricket%E2%80%99s%20overlords%2C%20its%20self-constituting%20national%20monopolies%2C%20not%20least%20the%20stern%20and%20reproving%20Board%20of%20Control%20for%20Cricket%20in%20India%20%E2%80%93%20to%20be%20one-out%20against%20leviathan%2C%20usually%20running%20the%20gauntlet%20of%20the%20press%2C%20and%20in%20doing%20so%20courting%20the%20suspicion%20of%20the%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESuresh%20Menon%E2%80%99s%20wonderful%20biography%2C%20%3Cem%3EBishan%3A%20Portrait%20of%20a%20Cricketer%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20collates%20a%20host%20of%20confrontations%20with%20the%20BCCI.%20During%20one%20Nagpur%20Test%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20the%20BCCI%20stuck%20Bishan%E2%80%99s%20team%20not%20in%20a%20hotel%20but%20in%20an%20MLA%20Hostel%20in%20which%20only%20he%20and%20the%20team%20manager%20had%20running%20water.%20Bishan%20remonstrated%20so%20fiercely%20with%20the%20local%20official%20that%20he%20was%20arraigned%20to%20appear%20before%20a%20BCCI%20disciplinary%20committee%20%E2%80%93%20sitting%2C%20by%20the%20way%2C%20in%20a%20five-star%20hotel%20in%20Mumbai.%20Having%20been%20reprimanded%2C%20Bishan%20learned%20that%20the%20BCCI%20had%20not%20booked%20his%20return%20tickets%20to%20Chandigarh%2C%20and%20there%20were%20no%20seats%20on%20the%20train.%20So%20it%20was%20that%20the%20captain%20of%20India%20travelled%20to%20a%20Duleep%20Trophy%20game%20bunked%20in%20a%20luggage%20rack%20for%201400%20km%2C%20then%20took%20a%20bus%20the%20last%20250%20km.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%E2%80%99ve%20called%20him%20Bishan%20here%20advisedly%2C%20because%20I%20did%20have%20the%20good%20fortune%20to%20know%20him%2C%20just%20a%20little%2C%20although%20with%20him%20it%20always%20felt%20like%20more.%20Such%20was%20his%20immediate%20warmth%3B%20it%20was%20like%20being%20wrapped%20in%20an%20instant%20hug.%20%E2%80%98You%20and%20Ray%20Robinson!%E2%80%99%20he%20said%20when%20we%20were%20first%20introduced%20in%20England%2015%20years%20ago.%20%E2%80%98My%20favourite%20Australian%20writers!%E2%80%99%20And%20much%20as%20I%20liked%20being%20recognised%2C%20I%20was%20the%20more%20chuffed%20by%20his%20reference%20to%20Ray%20Robbie%2C%20likewise%20my%20favourite%2C%20and%20something%20of%20a%20personal%20hero.%20Bishan%20had%20a%20capacity%20for%20immediate%2C%20easy%20intimacy%2C%20and%20a%20fund%20of%20earthy%20opinions%20expressed%20with%20an%20absolute%20unguardedness%2C%20whether%20about%20his%20reverence%20for%20the%20Nawab%20of%20Pataudi%20Junior%2C%20his%20ambivalent%20relations%20with%20Sunil%20Gavaskar%2C%20or%20his%20utter%20contempt%20for%20administrators%20generally.%20No%20coaching%20sinecure%20or%20commentator%E2%80%99s%20blazer%20for%20Bishan.%20He%20was%20absolutely%20his%20own%20man%2C%20proudly%20Indian%2C%20utterly%20cosmopolitan.%20Had%20the%20Australian%20Arthur%20Mailey%20not%20said%20already%20said%20it%2C%20after%20being%20criticised%20for%20advising%20the%20Englishman%20Ian%20Peebles%20in%201930%2C%20the%20remark%20could%20have%20come%20from%20Bishan%3A%20%E2%80%98Spin%20bowling%20is%20an%20art%2C%20and%20art%20is%20international.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHow%20dearly%20beloved%20he%20was%20too.%20I%20once%20had%20a%20night%20out%20with%20him%20at%20Delhi%20Golf%20Club%2C%20where%20he%20received%20a%20non-stop%20stream%20of%20well-wishers%20and%20petitioners%20as%20though%20they%20were%20personal%20friends%20%E2%80%93%20only%20to%20quietly%20confide%20that%20he%20had%20only%20the%20vaguest%20idea%20whom%20half%20of%20them%20were.%20When%20we%20came%20out%2C%20I%20thought%20that%20my%20driver%20was%20going%20to%20faint%20with%20excitement.%20%E2%80%98Naveen%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20so%20sorry%20to%20have%20kept%20you%20so%20late%2C%E2%80%99%20I%20said%20as%20we%20returned%20to%20the%20city.%20%E2%80%98Sir!%E2%80%99%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%98It%20was%20Bishan%20Bedi.%E2%80%99%20I%20had%20to%20pinch%20myself%20too.%20Good%20heavens%2C%20it%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EGideon%20Haigh%20has%20been%20a%20journalist%20for%20almost%20four%20decades%2C%20has%20published%20more%20than%2040%20books%20and%20contributed%20to%20more%20than%20100%20newspapers%20and%20magazines.%20He%20is%20also%20co-host%20of%20the%20podcast%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3ECricket%2C%20Et%20Cetera.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698116944000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F24083056%2FF9Hm3y3W0AAny2G.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsport%2Fbishan-singh-bedi-bowled-to-deceive-but-frank-and-big-hearted-was-the-least-deceptive-of-men%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22He%20brought%20a%20unique%20spirit%20to%20cricket%20%E2%80%93%20an%20expansiveness%20and%20chivalry.%20To%20face%20him%20must%20have%20been%20like%20having%20your%20pocket%20picked%20then%20given%20your%20wallet%20back.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A147%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsport%2Fbishan-singh-bedi-bowled-to-deceive-but-frank-and-big-hearted-was-the-least-deceptive-of-men%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Buddhism%20for%20Nehru%20Was%20About%20Building%20Diplomatic%20Alliances%2C%20for%20Ambedkar%20a%20Way%20to%20Liberate%20the%20Oppressed%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F23234645%2FBangkok.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EI%20read%20Douglas%20Ober%E2%80%99s%20work%20in%202016%20when%20it%20was%20still%20a%20dissertation%20with%20the%20University%20of%20British%20Columbia.%20I%20was%20thrilled%2C%20fascinated%20and%20full%20of%20admiration%20for%20what%20he%20had%20pulled%20off%20%E2%80%93%20an%20expansive%20history%20of%20ideas%2C%20anchored%20in%20unusual%20archival%20sources.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20now%20turned%20into%20a%20fine%20book%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnavayana.org%2Fproducts%2Fdust-on-the-throne%2F%3Fv%3Dc86ee0d9d7ed%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EDust%20on%20the%20Throne%3A%20The%20Search%20for%20Buddhism%20in%20Modern%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20was%20shortlisted%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cundillprize.com%2F2023shortlist%5C%22%3ECundill%20History%20Prize%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDust%20on%20the%20Throne%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0recovers%20the%20integral%20role%20of%20lesser-known%20Indian%20anti-caste%20activists%20and%20non-Indian%20Buddhist%20monastics%20in%20the%20making%20of%20modern%20global%20Buddhism.%20Ober%20also%20accounts%20for%20the%20powerful%20influence%20Buddhism%20exerted%20in%20shaping%20modern%20Indian%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEager%20to%20know%20more%20about%20arguments%20in%20the%20book%20that%20open%20up%20new%20directions%20for%20research%20and%20thought%20with%20regard%20to%20Buddhism%20in%20modern%20South%20Asia%2C%20I%20conducted%20this%20interview%20with%20him%20over%20email%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20270px)%2085vw%2C%20270px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F23225818%2FDUST-ON-THE-THRONE%25E2%2580%25949788195539291-cover-1-203x300.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22270%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F23225818%2FDUST-ON-THE-THRONE%25E2%2580%25949788195539291-cover-1-203x300.jpg%20203w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F23225818%2FDUST-ON-THE-THRONE%25E2%2580%25949788195539291-cover-1-692x1024.jpg%20692w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F23225818%2FDUST-ON-THE-THRONE%25E2%2580%25949788195539291-cover-1.jpg%20811w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-681450%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EDouglas%20Ober%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EDust%20on%20the%20Throne%3A%20The%20Search%20for%20Buddhism%20in%20Modern%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3ENavayana%20Publishing%20(2023)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EV.%20Geetha%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20your%20introduction%2C%20you%20point%20to%20the%20untenability%20of%20what%20has%20become%20%E2%80%98commonsense%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20that%20Buddhism%20had%20all%20but%20died%20in%20the%20Indian%20subcontinent%20until%20it%20was%20%E2%80%98rediscovered%E2%80%99%20in%20modern%20colonial%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EYou%20point%20to%20how%20such%20arguments%20need%20to%20be%20re-examined%2C%20and%20here%20you%20reference%20textual%20sources%20in%20diverse%20languages%20and%20across%20geographies%20in%20India.%20You%20go%20on%20to%20create%20a%20landscape%20of%20modern%20Buddhism%20as%20it%20has%20come%20to%20be%20from%20the%2018th%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECould%20you%20tell%20us%20about%20your%20use%20of%20multilingual%20sources%20and%20how%20you%20worked%20with%20original%20texts%20and%20translations%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDouglas%20Ober%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20One%20of%20the%20major%20challenges%20to%20the%20study%20of%20Buddhism%20during%20this%20period%20is%20that%20Buddhist%20works%20and%2For%20references%20to%20Buddhism%20were%20produced%20in%20a%20wide%20array%20of%20languages%20and%20scripts.%20We%E2%80%99re%20accustomed%20to%20thinking%20about%20South%20Asian%20Buddhism%20as%20something%20that%20is%20tied%20to%20so-called%20canonical%20languages%20like%20Pali%20and%20Sanskrit%2C%20but%20if%20we%20only%20focus%20on%20these%2C%20we%20risk%20losing%20sight%20of%20the%20bigger%20picture.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOnce%20I%20realised%20that%20I%20wanted%20to%20craft%20a%20pan-Indian%20and%20even%20global%20narrative%20and%20understand%20how%20ideas%20connected%20across%20regions%2C%20I%20chose%20to%20read%20widely%20rather%20than%20focus%20on%20just%20a%20few%20select%20texts%20or%20individuals.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMy%20own%20Asian%20language%20training%20was%20in%20Hindi%2C%20Tibetan%2C%20Sanskrit%20and%20Pali%20%E2%80%93%20so%20that%20was%20my%20base.%20I%20also%20drew%20on%20numerous%20translations%20from%20other%20languages%20into%20English%2C%20Hindi%20and%20French.%20In%20the%20end%2C%20the%20book%20drew%20on%20primary%20and%20secondary%20sources%20that%20had%20also%20been%20originally%20composed%20in%20Bengali%2C%20Burmese%2C%20French%2C%20Japanese%2C%20Malayalam%2C%20Marathi%2C%20Nepali%2C%20Persian%2C%20Russian%2C%20Tamil%2C%20Telugu%20and%20Urdu.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EObviously%2C%20I%20am%20standing%20on%20the%20shoulders%20of%20those%20who%20made%20those%20sources%20available%20to%20me%20%E2%80%93%20mostly%20in%20previously%20published%20works%20but%20also%20in%20archives%20and%20in%20a%20few%20cases%2C%20colleagues%20and%20friends%20who%20provided%20direct%20translations%20or%20summaries%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVG%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Today%2C%20the%20scholarship%20on%20modern%20Indian%20Buddhism%20focuses%20on%20conditions%20in%20Anglo-America%20and%20its%20various%20pathologies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20you%20have%20charted%20a%20new%20direction.%20You%20examine%20what%20%E2%80%98modern%E2%80%99%20Buddhism%20did%20for%2C%20and%20meant%20to%20Indian%20scholars%20of%20religion%2C%20amateur%20historians%20%E2%80%93%20those%20who%20took%20%3Cem%3Edeeksha%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20those%20from%20within%20existing%20and%20active%20Buddhist%20communities%2C%20and%20how%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20these%20diverse%20individuals%20and%20groups%20helped%20bring%20modern%20Buddhism%20into%20existence.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWas%20there%20a%20specific%20text%20or%20argument%20that%20you%20identified%20which%20set%20you%20off%20on%20this%20course%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Frethinking-manuscript-practices-in-india%5C%22%3ERethinking%20India%E2%80%99s%20Manuscript%20Practices%20as%20Official%20Policy%20Undervalues%20Its%20Rich%20Heritage%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDO%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20terms%20of%20secondary%20scholarship%2C%20I%20was%20greatly%20influenced%20by%20the%20turn%20to%20trans-regional%20networks%20and%20%E2%80%98translocative%20flows%E2%80%99%20by%20scholars%20like%20Thomas%20Tweed%2C%20Anne%20Blackburn%2C%20Richard%20Jaffe%2C%20Sanjay%20Subramanyam%20and%20Nile%20Green.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20before%20starting%20the%20research%2C%20I%20had%20been%20inspired%20by%20the%20Tibetan-language%20memoir%20of%20the%20Tibetan%20Buddhist%20savant%2C%20Gendun%20Chopel%2C%20who%20travelled%20to%20India%20from%20Tibet%20in%20the%201930s%20and%20mingled%20with%20many%20of%20Asia%E2%80%99s%20and%20Europe%E2%80%99s%20leading%20Buddhist%20figures%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EChopel%20led%20me%20to%20the%20Marxist%20scholar%20and%20sometimes%20Buddhist%20monk%2C%20Rahul%20Sankrityayan.%20As%20my%20research%20really%20began%20to%20unfold%2C%20I%20read%20the%20entirety%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FMeri_Jeevan_Yatra%5C%22%3ERahul%20Sankrityayan%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EMeri%20Jivan%20Yatra%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20used%20it%20to%20draw%20up%20a%20map%20of%20where%20Buddhism%20circulated%20during%20this%20period%20and%20how%20it%20shaped%20such%20a%20diverse%20social%20landscape.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20Meera%20Kosambi%20translated%20(from%20Marathi%20into%20English)%20many%20of%20the%20writings%20of%20her%20grandfather%2C%20Dharmanand%20Kosambi%20%E2%80%93%20the%20great%20Pali%20scholar%20and%20also%20sometimes%20Buddhist%20monk%20%E2%80%93%20I%20realised%20that%20there%20were%20all%20kinds%20of%20intellectual%2C%20social%20and%20political%20patterns%20that%20tied%20these%20histories%20together.%20I%20then%20set%20off%20to%20explore%20them%2C%20and%20as%20I%20did%2C%20a%20kind%20of%20map%20of%20Buddhism%20in%20modern%20Asia%20began%20to%20reveal%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVG%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20One%20of%20the%20things%20that%20fascinated%20me%20about%20your%20approach%20was%20your%20sense%20of%20wonder%20%E2%80%93%20at%20what%20workers%20in%20Buddhist%20sites%2C%20digging%20up%20or%20uncovering%20ruins%2C%20possibly%20made%20of%20what%20they%20were%20doing%2C%20and%20of%20local%20lore%20that%20might%20have%20engaged%20their%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fiyodhee-thass-pandithar-a-pioneer-in-dalit-history-and-literature%5C%22%3ETamil%20scholar%20Stalin%20Rajangam%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20noted%20that%20in%20almost%20all%20his%20wanderings%20through%20Jaina%20and%20Buddhist%20sites%20in%20the%20Tamil%20countryside%2C%20he%20has%20come%20across%20local%20histories%20which%20exist%20as%20forms%20of%20recall.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20since%20questioned%20the%20truth%20claims%20of%20sources%3A%20inscriptions%2C%20literature%2C%20local%20lore%2C%20diffuse%20public%20memory%20%E2%80%A6%20what%20they%20tell%20us%20or%20fail%20to%20tell%20us%20about%20Jaina%20and%20Buddhist%20presence%20in%20these%20landscapes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20context%2C%20your%20ruminations%20about%20the%20workers%20and%20their%20sense%20of%20the%20past%20pushes%20us%20to%20reflect%20on%20our%20own%20textual%20and%20other%20labour.%20What%20made%20you%20want%20to%20know%20more%20about%20those%20who%20helped%20%E2%80%98recover%E2%80%99%20Buddhist%20monuments%2C%20whose%20labour%20literally%20marks%20the%20%E2%80%98presence%E2%80%99%20of%20Buddhism%20in%20modern%20India%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fraja-sivaprasad-and-the-lost-history-of-buddhism%5C%22%3ERaja%20Sivaprasad%20and%20the%20Lost%20History%20of%20Buddhism%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDO%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Truth%20be%20told%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20not%20sure%20what%20led%20me%20to%20ask%20these%20kinds%20of%20questions.%20On%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20just%20a%20curious%20person%20and%20want%20to%20better%20understand%20what%20people%20think%20and%20why.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20I%20think%20some%20of%20this%20may%20have%20stemmed%20from%20my%20early%20training%20in%20religious%20studies%2C%20which%20was%20largely%20driven%20by%20anthropological%20approaches%20that%20cast%20a%20more%20critical%20eye%20on%20the%20role%20that%20text%20and%20doctrine%20played%20in%20everyday%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETwo%20of%20my%20early%20mentors%20(both%20of%20whom%20have%20now%20sadly%20passed)%2C%20Kyoko%20Tokuno%20(a%20historian%20of%20Chinese%20Buddhism)%20and%20Charles%20Keyes%20(an%20anthropologist%20of%20Theravada%20Buddhism)%2C%20always%20encouraged%20me%20to%20think%20beyond%20the%20text%20and%20question%20the%20relationship%20between%20the%20lived%20and%20textual%20tradition.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVG%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20While%20I%20think%20almost%20each%20of%20your%20chapters%20contains%20themes%20that%20can%20fill%20an%20entire%20a%20book%2C%20some%20are%20particularly%20significant%3A%20I%20was%20wondering%20if%20you%20could%20tell%20us%20a%20little%20more%20about%20each%20of%20these.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETake%20the%20chapter%20on%20the%20Hinduising%20of%20Buddhism%3A%20here%2C%20you%20have%20meticulously%20dealt%20with%20the%20role%20played%20by%20individuals%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FJugal_Kishore_Birla%5C%22%3EJugal%20Kishore%20Birla%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Given%20how%20the%20Buddha%20and%20Buddhism%20have%20shadowed%20philosophical%20traditions%20antithetical%20to%20what%20they%20stood%20for%2C%20do%20you%20see%20this%20manner%20of%20Hinduising%20as%20a%20moment%20in%20this%20long%20history%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOr%20did%20it%20have%20to%20do%20as%20much%20with%20an%20anti-colonial%20politics%2C%20which%20sought%20to%20%E2%80%98recover%E2%80%99%20a%20worthy%20golden%20age%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDO%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20think%20it%20has%20to%20do%20with%20both.%20There%20is%20a%20real%20resonance%20between%20the%20medieval%20appropriation%20of%20the%20Buddha%20via%20the%20Vishnu%20avatar%20and%20the%20modern%20Hindu%20appropriation%20of%20the%20Buddha%20as%20a%20great%20Hindu%20social%20reformer.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBoth%20developments%20emerged%20out%20of%20long-standing%20debates%20between%20Brahmins%20and%20Buddhists%2C%20as%20well%20as%20local%20political%20conditions%2C%20and%20real%20and%20imagined%20threats.%20So%2C%20there%20is%20real%20continuity%20here%20and%20the%20colonial-era%20Indians%20who%20worked%20to%20Brahmanise%20Buddhism%20were%20well%20aware%20of%20this%20longer%20history%20and%20looked%20to%20it%20for%20inspiration%20and%20guidance.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Freligion%2Fconversion-hinduism-buddhism-modi%5C%22%3EAmidst%20%E2%80%98Conversion%E2%80%99%20Brouhaha%2C%20PM%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20Words%20in%20Bali%20Cement%20a%20Truth%20About%20Hinduism%E2%80%99s%20Spread%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20are%20distinctive%20differences%2C%20which%20as%20you%20mention%2C%20were%20tied%20to%20anti-colonial%20politics%2C%20the%20nationalist%20fetish%20for%20a%20glorious%20past%20and%20%5Bthe%5D%20question%20of%20how%20a%20Hindu%20nation%20would%20fit%20into%20a%20modern%20Asian%20world%20that%20was%20increasingly%20imagined%20as%20Buddhist.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20think%20these%20external%20pressures%20of%20anti-colonialism%20and%20pan-Asianism%2C%20along%20with%20the%20growing%20resonance%20that%20Buddhism%20held%20among%20anti-caste%20leaders%20in%20India%2C%20created%20a%20sense%20of%20urgency%20that%20this%20so-called%20Buddhist%20revival%20needed%20to%20be%20addressed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVG%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Within%20South%20Asia%2C%20there%20were%20different%20approaches%20at%20making%20Buddhism%20relevant%20and%20claiming%20it%20as%20worthwhile%20tradition.%20Like%20you%20write%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20attend%20to%20vernacular%20articulations%20of%20Buddhism%20to%20get%20a%20sense%20of%20its%20continued%20presence.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHow%20might%20one%20think%20of%20Buddhism%20in%20the%20modern%20period%20then%3F%20Are%20these%20different%20ways%20of%20thinking%20about%20Buddhism%20variations%20on%20a%20set%20of%20common%20themes%3F%20Or%20do%20they%20signify%20distinctive%20approaches%2C%20shaped%20by%20specific%20histories%20and%20geographies%3F%20If%20so%2C%20what%20renders%20these%20projects%20%E2%80%98equally%E2%80%99%20modern%3F%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDO%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Local%20histories%20and%20their%20interactions%20with%20other%20cultural%20and%20religious%20traditions%20have%20always%20played%20a%20significant%20role%20in%20shaping%20the%20way%20Buddhism%20is%20practiced%20and%20understood.%20Yet%20despite%20the%20diversity%20of%20approaches%2C%20many%20of%20these%20adaptations%20of%20Buddhism%20retain%20core%20Buddhist%20principles%20and%20practices%2C%20and%20the%20ethical%20and%20philosophical%20teachings%20are%20preserved%2C%20albeit%20in%20different%20forms.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20tension%20here%2C%20of%20course.%20Who%20is%20to%20say%20what%20the%20%E2%80%98essence%E2%80%99%20is%3F%20At%20what%20point%20has%20something%20deviated%20too%20far%20from%20those%20essential%20principles%20and%20practices%3F%20It%20is%20in%20those%20tensions%20that%20we%20can%20often%20best%20understand%20what%20constitutes%20a%20Buddhist%20tradition.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20of%20modernity%20is%20exceedingly%20complex%20but%20in%20its%20simplest%20formation%2C%20I%E2%80%99d%20argue%20that%20what%20renders%20these%20traditions%20modern%20is%20their%20adaptation%20to%20contemporary%20circumstances%20and%20their%20continued%20connections%20to%20the%20past.%20That%20adaptability%20is%20the%20hallmark%20of%20Buddhist%20history%2C%20of%20the%20Buddha%E2%80%99s%20skilful%20means%20or%20method%20(%3Cem%3Eupaya%3C%2Fem%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVG%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20From%20archival%20and%20other%20sources%20you%20have%20assembled%2C%20it%20is%20evident%20that%20the%20concern%20with%20the%20past%2C%20with%20a%20putative%20golden%20age%2C%20had%20not%20only%20to%20do%20with%20%E2%80%98the%20wonder%20that%20was%20India%E2%80%99%2C%20but%20with%20a%20time%20that%20resonated%20with%20modern%20values%2C%20especially%20of%20equality%2C%20justice%20and%20fraternity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EYour%20book%20asks%20us%20to%20rethink%20the%20historiographical%20concerns%20of%20late%20colonial%20India.%20So%2C%20the%20debates%20of%20the%20time%20did%20not%20only%C2%A0have%20to%20do%20with%20civilisational%20%E2%80%98differences%E2%80%99%20(Aryan%20vs.%20Dravidian%3B%20%3Cem%3Emulnivasi%3C%2Fem%3E%20vs.%20settlers)%3B%20or%20authentic%20and%20alien%20rule%20(%E2%80%98Hindu%E2%80%99%20India%20vs%20%E2%80%98Muslim%E2%80%99%20India).%20They%20also%20had%20to%20do%20with%20philosophical%20traditions%20that%20were%20claimed%20as%20their%20own%20by%20a%20host%20of%20anti-caste%20radicals.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fhow-hindutva-historiography-is-rooted-in-the-colonial-view-of-indian-history%5C%22%3EHow%20Hindutva%20Historiography%20is%20Rooted%20in%20the%20Colonial%20View%20of%20Indian%20History%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20was%20reading%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbrill.com%2Fview%2Fjournals%2Fsaih%2Faop%2Farticle-10.1163-25425552-12340042%2Farticle-10.1163-25425552-12340042.xml%3Flanguage%3Den%5C%22%3EEric%20Gurevitch%E2%80%99s%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20Jaina%20debates%20on%20caste%20in%20the%20western%20Chalukyan%20courts%20and%20it%20is%20evident%20that%20the%20%3Cem%3Esramana%3C%2Fem%3E%20traditions%20had%20things%20to%20say%20which%20modern%20anti-caste%20radicals%20found%20attractive.%20In%20this%20sense%2C%20any%20study%20of%20modern%20Indian%20thought%20must%20necessarily%20include%20Iyothee%20Thass%2C%20Bodhanand%2C%20Dharmanand%20Kosambi%E2%80%A6%20would%20you%20like%20to%20reflect%20on%20this%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDO%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20You%E2%80%99re%20absolutely%20right%3A%20whether%20it%20was%20a%20reimagining%20of%20the%20Buddha%20as%20a%20champion%20of%20social%20justice%20or%20an%20exploration%20of%20ancient%20texts%20for%20egalitarian%20ideas%2C%20there%20was%20a%20strong%20connection%20between%20the%20past%20and%20the%20ideals%20of%20the%20present.%20The%20%3Cem%3Esramana%3C%2Fem%3E%20traditions%20often%20had%20a%20history%20of%20challenging%20established%20hierarchies.%20Modern%20leaders%20drew%20on%20them%20to%20advocate%20for%20social%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAll%20societies%20have%20their%20fracture%20lines%2C%20whether%20it%E2%80%99s%20questions%20of%20foreign%20rule%2C%20or%20settlers%20versus%20natives%2C%20civilisational%20differences%20and%20so%20on%2C%20but%20I%20think%20the%20works%20of%20towering%20intellectuals%20like%20Thass%2C%20Kosambi%20and%20others%20make%20clear%20that%20these%20were%20also%20questions%20deeply%20intertwined%20with%20values%20of%20equality%2C%20justice%20and%20fraternity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20rich%20philosophical%20heritage%20resonates%20with%20these%20values%20and%20if%20we%20want%20to%20better%20understand%20not%20only%20the%20subcontinent%E2%80%99s%20history%20but%20also%20the%20historiographical%20concerns%20of%20late%20colonial%20India%2C%20we%20must%20take%20them%20seriously.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVG%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20chapter%20on%20Buddhism%20and%20the%20socialist%20imagination%20is%20rich%2C%20and%20I%20was%20wondering%20what%20you%20think%20of%20this%20in%20the%20context%20of%20other%20such%20efforts%20that%20link%20labour%2C%20the%20working%20class%20and%20Buddhism%3A%20for%20instance%20Laurence%20Cox%E2%80%99s%20(with%20Alicia%20Turner%20and%20Brian%20Bocking)%20book%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faeon.co%2Fessays%2Fu-dhammaloka-the-irish-buddhist-monk-who-faced-down-imperialism%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Irish%20Buddhist%3A%20the%20Forgotten%20Monk%20who%20Faced%20Down%20the%20British%20Empire%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDO%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20am%20a%20huge%20admirer%20of%20Laurence%20Cox%E2%80%99s%20scholarship%20and%20I%20remain%20greatly%20inspired%20by%20the%20model%20of%20%E2%80%9Cplebeian%20cosmopolitanism%E2%80%9D%20that%20Cox%2C%20Turner%20and%20Bocking%20put%20forth%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Irish%20Buddhist%3C%2Fem%3E.%20I%20think%20the%20entire%20U%20Dhammaloka%20project%20(out%20of%20which%20it%20emerged)%20has%20opened%20so%20many%20new%20avenues%20for%20understanding%20Buddhism%E2%80%99s%2020th%20century%20connections%20to%20the%20working%20classes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%20combined%20with%20the%20insights%20provided%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.orientblackswan.com%2Fdetails%3Fid%3D9788125037019%5C%22%3EHarald%20Fischer-Tin%C3%A9%E2%80%99s%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20race%2C%20class%20and%20white%20subalternity%20in%20colonial%20India%2C%20I%20think%20an%20entirely%20new%20sub-field%20could%20be%20created.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJust%20consider%20the%20Irish%20Buddhist%20radicals%20who%20worked%20with%20Tamil%20Buddhist%20migrants%20and%20labourers%20in%20early%2020th-century%20India%20in%20places%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbuddhistcentrekgf.com%2F%5C%22%3EKolar%20Gold%20Fields%3C%2Fa%3E.%20There%20is%20so%20little%20we%20know%20about%20these%20connections%20%E2%80%A6%20but%20it%20has%20all%20the%20makings%20of%20an%20Amitav%20Ghosh%20novel!%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVG%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Lastly%3A%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20Buddhist%20diplomacy%20gave%20an%20entirely%20new%20twist%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epw.in%2Fjournal%2F2016%2F1%2Fperspectives%2Fbrief-history-panchsheel.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98panchsheel%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20non-aligned%20movement%2C%20and%20this%20contrasts%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Fpageturner%2Fcentral-railways-sent-special-train-museum-gave-statue-for-ambedkars-buddhism-conversion%2F1801057%2F%5C%22%3EAmbedkar%E2%80%99s%20world-transforming%20project%20of%20taking%20deeksha%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20nearly%20half%20a%20million%20followers.%20The%20former%20seems%20an%20exercise%20in%20anti-colonial%20worldmaking%20and%20diplomacy%2C%20and%20the%20latter%20stakes%20claims%20on%20a%20utopia%20and%20on%20reconstructing%20the%20world.%20Could%20you%20comment%20on%20this%20contrast%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDO%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20think%20you%20are%20right%3A%20these%20are%20two%20different%20approaches%20at%20addressing%20the%20challenges%20in%20post-colonial%20India%20and%20engaging%20with%20the%20global%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBoth%20drew%20from%20common%20pools%20of%20thought%2C%20but%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20Buddhist%20vision%20was%20primarily%20an%20exercise%20in%20building%20diplomatic%20alliances%20with%20other%20Asian%20states%2C%20securing%20loyalty%20at%20the%20borders%20and%20advocating%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20central%20place%20in%20a%20very%20volatile%20postcolonial%20Asia.%20Nehru%20possessed%20the%20reins%20of%20power%20and%20had%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20resources%20at%20his%20fingertips%20in%20order%20to%20execute%20these%20plans%20but%20pragmatic%20realities%20also%20checked%20his%20idealism.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmbedkar%E2%80%99s%20Buddhist%20vision%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20was%20a%20radical%20endeavour%20steeped%20in%20both%20existential%20and%20political%20convictions%20%E2%80%93%20a%20deep-seated%20faith%20if%20you%20will.%20It%20aimed%20to%20not%20only%20liberate%20the%20marginalised%20and%20oppressed%20castes%20but%20overthrow%20the%20established%20social%20and%20(im)moral%20order%2C%20as%20he%20had%20experienced%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20wished%20to%20reconstruct%20the%20world%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20equality%2C%20fraternity%20and%20justice%3A%20values%20that%20resonated%20as%20much%20in%20the%20deep%20philosophical%20heritage%20of%20India%20as%20in%20the%20Enlightenment%20values%20of%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fv-geetha%5C%22%3EV.%20Geetha%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20feminist%20historian%2C%20writer%20and%20translator.%20She%20is%20the%20editorial%20director%2C%20Tara%20Books.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698114657000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F23234645%2FBangkok.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fdouglas-ober-dust-on-the-throne-interview-transcript%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Douglas%20Ober%2C%20author%20of%20%E2%80%98Dust%20on%20the%20Throne%3A%20The%20Search%20for%20Buddhism%20in%20Modern%20India%E2%80%99%2C%20tells%20V.%20Geetha%20about%20his%20examination%20of%20%E2%80%98modern%E2%80%99%20Buddhism%2C%20the%20Hinduising%20of%20Buddhism%2C%20the%20contrast%20between%20Nehru%20and%20Ambedkar's%20Buddhist%20visions%20and%20more.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fdouglas-ober-dust-on-the-throne-interview-transcript%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22At%20least%20seven%20dead%20and%20dozens%20injured%20after%20'super%20fog'%20causes%20multiple%20pile-ups%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698095340000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F10%2F768x432%2Fskynews-louisiana-fog-manchac_6333391.jpg%3F20231024080549%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fnew-orleans-super-fog-leaves-at-least-two-dead-and-dozens-injured-in-multiple-pile-ups-12991332%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22At%20least%20seven%20people%20are%20dead%20and%2030%20injured%20after%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bsuper%20fog%26quot%3B%20caused%20more%20than%20two%20dozen%20traffic%20pile-ups%20on%20a%20US%20highway.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A104%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fnew-orleans-super-fog-leaves-at-least-two-dead-and-dozens-injured-in-multiple-pile-ups-12991332%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fnew-orleans-super-fog-leaves-at-least-two-dead-and-dozens-injured-in-multiple-pile-ups-12991332%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fnew-orleans-super-fog-leaves-at-least-two-dead-and-dozens-injured-in-multiple-pile-ups-12991332%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bishan%20Singh%20Bedi%20Was%20Full%20of%20Life%20and%20Genuinely%20Cared%20for%20His%20People%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F23233659%2FThe-Wire-52.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EOne%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20greatest%20cricketers%20Bishan%20Singh%20Bedi%20(77)%20breathed%20his%20last%20on%20Monday%2C%20October%2023.%20The%20following%20is%20an%20excerpt%20from%20%3C%2Fem%3EMid-Wicket%20Tales%3Cem%3E%2C%20a%20book%20by%20S.%20Giridhar%20and%20V.%20J.%20Raghunath%20published%20in%202014%2C%20and%20returning%20in%20a%20revised%20and%20expanded%20edition%20with%20Speaking%20Tiger%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E.%20The%20particular%20chapter%20in%20the%20book%20%E2%80%93%20Bishan%20Singh%20Bedi%3A%20Of%20Large%20Hearts%20and%20Large%20Stories%20%E2%80%93%20presents%20the%20warmed-hearted%20personality%20of%20Bedi.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESome%20months%20after%20%3Cem%3EMid-wicket%20Tales%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehad%20been%20published%2C%C2%A0Gideon%20Haigh%2C%20the%20cricket%20historian%20from%C2%A0%C2%A0%20Australia%2C%20wrote%20a%20generous%20review.%20He%20also%20sent%20it%20to%20his%20good%20friend%20in%20Delhi%2C%20the%20legendary%20cricketer%2C%20Bishan%20Singh%20Bedi.%20Gideon%20asked%20me%20to%20send%20Bedi%20a%20copy%2C%20which%20I%20(Giridhar)%20did%20with%20alacrity.%20Two%20days%20later%2C%20my%20phone%20rang.%20It%20was%20Bedi%2C%20exuberant%20and%20in%20his%20characteristic%20drawl%2C%20telling%20me%20he%20loved%20the%20book.%20I%20asked%20him%2C%20have%20you%20read%20it%20already%3F%20To%20which%20he%20replied%20he%20had%20only%20read%20a%20few%20chapters%20but%20liked%20what%20he%20had%20read%20so%20much%20that%20he%20had%20to%20immediately%20compliment%20us.%20I%20introduced%20him%20to%20Raghunath%20over%20email.%20Raghu%20was%20visiting%20his%20daughter%20in%20Delhi%20at%20that%20time%20and%20even%20before%20one%20could%20whip%20the%20bails%20off%20to%20a%20Bedi%20delivery%2C%20Raghu%20was%20having%20dinner%20at%20Bedi%E2%80%99s%20farmhouse!%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20Raghu%20met%20Bedi%20that%20first%20time%2C%20we%20had%20just%20begun%20work%20on%20our%20second%20book%2C%20%3Cem%3EFrom%20Mumbai%20to%20Durban%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20would%20narrate%20the%20history%20of%20Indian%20Test%20cricket%20through%20the%20stories%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20greatest%20Test%20matches.%20As%20part%20of%20our%20research%20at%20that%20time%2C%20we%20were%20reaching%20out%20to%20cricketers%20and%20journalists%20to%20get%20their%20first-hand%20views%2C%20anecdotes%20and%20interesting%20snippets%20that%20would%20embellish%20the%20narration.%20That%20evening%20with%20Bedi%20was%20the%20first%20of%20our%20meetings%20with%20him.%20We%20did%20not%20have%20to%20persuade%20him%20because%20he%20had%20already%20made%20up%20his%20mind%20to%20help%20us.%20If%20you%C2%A0have%20browsed%20through%20the%20book%2C%20you%20will%20realise%20how%20much%20the%20great%20left-arm%20spinner%20contributed%20to%20it.%20He%20simply%20gave.%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20he%20even%20remembers%20how%20much%20he%20told%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20November%202015%2C%20Chennai%20was%20devastated%20by%20floods%2C%20rendering%20many%20people%20homeless.%20Lives%20were%20lost%2C%20houses%20ravaged.%20Bedi%2C%20living%20in%20Delhi%2C%20was%20getting%20desperately%20worried%20about%20his%20friends%20in%20Chennai.%20Not%20getting%20through%20to%20these%20people%20in%20Chennai%2C%20he%20called%20me%20to%20ask%20if%20his%20cricketer%20friends%20%E2%80%93%20W.%20V.%20Raman%2C%20Srikkanth%2C%20and%20a%20few%20others%20%E2%80%93%20and%20his%20new%20friend%2C%20Raghu%2C%20were%20safe.%20I%20had%20to%20admit%20that%20I%20did%20not%20know%20about%20the%20cricketers%20but%20assured%20him%20that%20Raghu%20was%20safe.%20Bedi%20was%20distraught%20and%20rang%20off%20to%20check%20with%20some%20other%20friends.%20That%E2%80%99s%20how%20Bedi%20is%20wired%2C%20genuinely%20concerned%20about%20his%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnder%20happier%20circumstances%20some%20months%20later%2C%20I%20got%20a%20call%20one%20evening%20at%209%20p.m.%20%E2%80%98Bishan%20here.%20I%20am%20in%20your%20town%2C%20at%20the%20Leela.%20Want%20to%20come%20over%20for%20dinner%3F%E2%80%99%20Since%20I%20live%20very%20close%20to%20The%20Leela%2C%20I%20was%20ringing%20his%20doorbell%20within%20minutes.%20Bedi%20welcomed%20me%20with%20a%20hug.%20And%20then%20mischievously%20he%20pointed%20me%20towards%20the%20shadowy%20corner%20of%20the%20room.%20Leaning%20against%20the%20wall%20was%20Sunil%20Joshi%2C%20former%20India%20left-arm%20spinner%20and%20in%20some%20ways%2C%20Bedi%E2%80%99s%20prot%C3%A9g%C3%A9.%20I%20told%20Bedi%20that%20like%20a%20good%20South%20Indian%2C%20I%20had%20finished%20dinner%20much%20before%20his%20call%20came.%20So%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%98Ok%20have%20a%20beer.%E2%80%99%20Then%20rubbing%20his%20hands%20and%20leaning%20in%20his%20luxurious%20chair%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%98When%20Sunil%20dropped%20in%20to%20see%20me%2C%20I%20thought%20I%20will%20call%20you%20over%20so%20that%20you%20can%20press%20him%20for%20some%20stories%20too.%E2%80%99%20Sunil%20of%20course%20is%20a%20lovely%20raconteur%20with%20an%20impish%20sense%20of%20humor.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20set%20up%20a%20meeting%20for%20a%20later%20day%20where%20he%20shared%20some%20lovely%20stories%2C%20which%20you%20will%20also%20find%20in%20the%20book.%20That%20evening%20at%20The%20Leela%2C%20Bedi%20was%20in%20form.%20He%20told%20of%20his%20love%20for%20players%20like%20Pataudi%20and%20Jaisimha%3B%20of%20the%20spirit%20in%20which%20sport%20must%20be%20played.%20He%20narrated%20stories%20from%20the%20Indian%20tours%20to%20the%20West%20Indies%20and%20Pakistan%3B%20told%20us%20about%20a%20crazy%20helicopter%20ride%20in%20Guyana%3B%20and%20about%20a%20nervous%20Jaisimha%20always%20smoking%20like%20a%20chimney%20before%20his%20turn%20to%20bat.%20Then%2C%20with%20loud%20guffaws%2C%20he%20told%20us%20wicked%20stories%20about%20Lala%20Amarnath%20and%20his%20endless%20bragging.%20In%20the%20middle%20of%20all%20that%20he%20also%20chided%20me%20(and%20Raghunath%20in%20his%20absence)%20of%20not%20being%20forthright%20and%20critical%20enough%20about%20dubious%20bowling%20actions%20in%20our%20earlier%20book.%20He%20said%20we%20were%20being%20unnecessarily%20politically%20correct%20while%20talking%20of%20Muralitharan%20in%20our%20chapter%20on%20great%20off-spinners.%20Time%20flew%20as%20I%20soaked%20in%20the%20stories%2C%20and%20it%20was%20well%20past%20midnight%20when%20I%20reached%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20manuscript%20of%20our%20book%20%3Cem%3EFrom%20Mumbai%20to%20Durban%20%3C%2Fem%3Ereached%20its%20final%20stages%2C%20I%20emailed%20Bedi%20to%20reconfirm%20some%20of%20the%20stories%20and%20facts%20that%20he%20had%20told%20us.%20Raghu%20and%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20sure%20we%20would%20not%20be%20misquoting%20him.%20One%20of%20those%20really%20tall%20tales%20was%20about%20Lala%20Amarnath%E2%80%99s%20boast%20of%20doing%2010%2C000%20skips%20with%20the%20skipping%20rope%20in%2030%20minutes.%20We%20feared%20we%20might%20not%20have%20got%20the%20number%20right.%20Bishan%20is%20not%20so%20prompt%20on%20email%20and%20it%20was%20easier%20to%20speak%20to%20him%20over%20phone.%20As%20we%20repeated%20our%20query%2C%20he%20interjected%20to%20say%2C%20%E2%80%98Nah%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%2030%2C000%20that%20Lala%20claimed%20not%2010%2C000%20skips.%E2%80%99%20So%20what%20we%20thought%20was%20an%20already%20tall%20tale%20only%20became%20taller%20when%20we%20went%20back%20to%20Bedi%20to%20reconfirm.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThat%E2%80%99s%20the%20fun%20of%20being%20acquainted%20with%20Bedi.%20We%20are%20pretty%20sure%20he%20is%20the%20same%20with%20almost%20everyone%2C%20friendly%20within%20minutes%20of%20shaking%20hands.%20That%20heart%2C%20it%20is%20large%2C%20it%20is%20generous%2C%20it%20overflows.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698085320000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F23233659%2FThe-Wire-52.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsport%2Fbishan-singh-bedi-was-full-of-life-and-genuinely-cared-for-his-people%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%20excerpt%20from%20the%20book%20'Mid-Wicket%20Tales'%20presents%20the%20warmed-hearted%20personality%20of%20Bedi%2C%20his%20love%20for%20players%20Pataudi%20and%20Jaisimha%2C%20stories%20from%20his%20tours%20to%20the%20West%20Indies%20and%20Pakistan%2C%20and%20about%20his%20crazy%20helicopter%20ride%20in%20Guyana.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A17%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsport%2Fbishan-singh-bedi-was-full-of-life-and-genuinely-cared-for-his-people%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Auto%20Workers%20Strike%20At%20Stellantis%E2%80%99%20Ram%20Pickup%20Plant%20In%